1
00:00:25,951 --> 00:00:28,954
SIX SINGLES UNDER ONE ROOF

2
00:00:30,289 --> 00:00:32,258
<i>This feels like a birthday party.</i>

3
00:00:32,324 --> 00:00:33,359
<i>Yeah, I get what you mean.</i>

4
00:00:33,425 --> 00:00:34,793
<i>- Back in school...</i>
<i>- A class rep's party?</i>

5
00:00:34,860 --> 00:00:36,328
<i>- Yeah.</i>
<i>- A rich kid's party.</i>

6
00:00:36,695 --> 00:00:38,197
So what are we doing tomorrow?

7
00:00:39,331 --> 00:00:40,432
Tomorrow?

8
00:00:40,499 --> 00:00:41,767
WHAT SHOULD WE DO?

9
00:00:42,001 --> 00:00:43,836
- I'm just not sure.
- What should we do?

10
00:00:44,637 --> 00:00:45,905
- It's tricky.
- Totally.

11
00:00:46,705 --> 00:00:48,974
I have one suggestion, though.

12
00:00:49,041 --> 00:00:51,510
Let's stay at home if possible.

13
00:00:52,444 --> 00:00:53,979
To make the most of our time here?

14
00:00:54,380 --> 00:00:56,148
- Yes, exactly.
- Goodness.

15
00:00:56,215 --> 00:00:58,717
- Seriously...
- Let's try to stay home.

16
00:00:59,118 --> 00:01:00,386
- Something along that line?
- Yeah.

17
00:01:00,452 --> 00:01:01,620
THEY DECIDED TO STAY HOME TOMORROW

18
00:01:02,021 --> 00:01:03,522
THINKS IT OVER

19
00:01:03,589 --> 00:01:05,291
If we're not leaving the house

20
00:01:05,357 --> 00:01:06,759
- everything has to happen here.
- Exactly.

21
00:01:06,825 --> 00:01:08,427
That's what I want. It's just...

22
00:01:08,494 --> 00:01:10,029
WHAT IS HE PLANNING THIS TIME?

23
00:01:10,563 --> 00:01:14,066
WHAT SHOULD I COOK TOMORROW?

24
00:01:14,133 --> 00:01:16,402
MASTER PARTY PLANNER'S EXPLOITS

25
00:01:16,468 --> 00:01:18,871
1. GIANT OCTOPUS

26
00:01:18,938 --> 00:01:22,041
2. CONVEYOR BELT SUSHI AT HOME

27
00:01:22,241 --> 00:01:26,011
AP'S OUT-OF-THE-BOX IDEAS
ARE ON ANOTHER LEVEL

28
00:01:26,512 --> 00:01:30,249
ALWAYS CONSIDERING
OPTIONS FOR A BIG FEAST

29
00:01:30,316 --> 00:01:33,018
WHAT IS HE PLANNING NOW?

30
00:01:33,085 --> 00:01:35,521
I think you can rest up now.

31
00:01:35,588 --> 00:01:36,889
The sushi train was enough.

32
00:01:37,890 --> 00:01:41,026
THANKS

33
00:01:41,493 --> 00:01:42,561
She's right.

34
00:01:42,628 --> 00:01:43,796
WE'VE HAD ENOUGH OF YOUR EVENTS

35
00:01:44,196 --> 00:01:45,497
DEEP IN THOUGHT

36
00:01:45,564 --> 00:01:46,832
How's this?

37
00:01:47,967 --> 00:01:49,501
Why don't we each invite

38
00:01:49,568 --> 00:01:52,471
a best friend home?

39
00:01:53,439 --> 00:01:55,107
We're inviting a friend here?

40
00:01:55,908 --> 00:01:59,912
When I told my friends
about this show

41
00:01:59,979 --> 00:02:01,480
so many of them wanted to know

42
00:02:01,547 --> 00:02:03,148
about the people I'd be staying with

43
00:02:03,215 --> 00:02:04,984
and what we'd be doing together.

44
00:02:05,050 --> 00:02:07,453
- It is a place worth showing off.
- You're right.

45
00:02:07,519 --> 00:02:08,787
I want to take them around the place.

46
00:02:08,854 --> 00:02:11,457
If you guys are up for it

47
00:02:11,523 --> 00:02:13,959
- I'd like to invite people over.
- I'm in.

48
00:02:14,026 --> 00:02:17,463
It's a chance for us to get to know
each other's close friends.

49
00:02:17,529 --> 00:02:18,530
That's a nice bonus.

50
00:02:18,998 --> 00:02:20,199
I'm in, too.

51
00:02:20,265 --> 00:02:21,266
LET'S EXPAND OUR SOCIAL CIRCLE

52
00:02:21,333 --> 00:02:22,601
Can you think of anyone to invite?

53
00:02:23,836 --> 00:02:25,104
Can you think of anyone to invite?

54
00:02:28,741 --> 00:02:30,743
AT THIS HOUR

55
00:02:30,809 --> 00:02:32,111
AND AT OUR AGE?

56
00:02:32,177 --> 00:02:33,779
- Let's see.
- I'll need to check.

57
00:02:34,346 --> 00:02:35,414
Let's do that.

58
00:02:35,481 --> 00:02:36,482
WHO WOULD BE AVAILABLE?

59
00:02:36,548 --> 00:02:38,884
- No one comes to mind this instant.
- Everyone is welcome.

60
00:02:38,951 --> 00:02:41,587
If we were still in our 20s

61
00:02:41,654 --> 00:02:44,256
we would have no trouble
inviting friends over.

62
00:02:44,323 --> 00:02:47,059
I could call anyone at this hour
and still get a yes back in the day.

63
00:02:47,126 --> 00:02:51,430
Yes, but we've aged over the years.

64
00:02:51,497 --> 00:02:53,699
Many have families of their own

65
00:02:53,766 --> 00:02:55,567
- So true.
- and work to manage as well.

66
00:02:55,634 --> 00:02:57,369
It feels like my social circle

67
00:02:57,436 --> 00:02:59,605
is shrinking little by little.

68
00:03:00,472 --> 00:03:02,841
Totally.

69
00:03:03,075 --> 00:03:05,577
Your social circle may shrink,
but the friendship deepens.

70
00:03:05,644 --> 00:03:07,012
- It sure does.
- Totally.

71
00:03:07,079 --> 00:03:08,313
Every friend means so much to you.

72
00:03:08,380 --> 00:03:09,782
THAT'S TRUE

73
00:03:09,848 --> 00:03:10,949
Friends...

74
00:03:11,517 --> 00:03:12,518
But...

75
00:03:12,584 --> 00:03:13,786
WHO SHOULD I CALL?

76
00:03:14,053 --> 00:03:15,988
DAZED

77
00:03:16,655 --> 00:03:19,491
WE'D GET A FEW GUESTS, RIGHT?

78
00:03:19,692 --> 00:03:21,293
- We'll need to contact our friends.
- Yeah.

79
00:03:21,360 --> 00:03:23,696
- Not everyone might be available.
- Exactly.

80
00:03:24,029 --> 00:03:25,030
You think so?

81
00:03:25,898 --> 00:03:27,099
Should I try contacting them?

82
00:03:28,567 --> 00:03:30,636
Who should I invite?
Let me check who I can call.

83
00:03:30,703 --> 00:03:32,104
RUSHING TO CONTACT THEIR BESTIES

84
00:03:33,138 --> 00:03:37,009
HIS FINGERS ARE BUSY
GOING THROUGH HIS CONTACT LIST

85
00:03:37,376 --> 00:03:39,144
- You've got so many friends.
- Well, yeah.

86
00:03:39,211 --> 00:03:40,979
- That's easily over 400.
- How many friends does he have?

87
00:03:41,246 --> 00:03:43,115
I'm not sure who might be available.

88
00:03:44,783 --> 00:03:49,021
EVERYONE IS SERIOUS
ABOUT LAST-MINUTE INVITES

89
00:03:49,221 --> 00:03:51,857
The friend I have in mind

90
00:03:52,157 --> 00:03:53,158
is a woman.

91
00:03:53,692 --> 00:03:54,760
INTEREST PIQUED

92
00:03:54,827 --> 00:03:55,928
Really?

93
00:03:56,228 --> 00:03:57,296
She looks like a cat.

94
00:03:59,231 --> 00:04:00,232
Seriously?

95
00:04:00,632 --> 00:04:02,501
He suddenly went, "Seriously?"

96
00:04:02,568 --> 00:04:05,704
Their looks changed
with anticipation.

97
00:04:06,105 --> 00:04:07,873
- Really?
- You like girls who look like cats?

98
00:04:07,940 --> 00:04:10,342
- I do.
- She looks like a cat.

99
00:04:12,544 --> 00:04:14,012
My friend loves Keun-suk.

100
00:04:14,079 --> 00:04:15,314
My friend loves Keun-suk.

101
00:04:15,380 --> 00:04:16,381
SLIGHT SMILE

102
00:04:16,448 --> 00:04:19,017
You're just messing with me again
with false hope.

103
00:04:19,084 --> 00:04:20,352
No, it's not like that at all.

104
00:04:20,853 --> 00:04:22,154
What's going on?

105
00:04:22,221 --> 00:04:23,288
SECOND-HAND DOPAMINE RUSH

106
00:04:23,489 --> 00:04:27,326
She wanted to get to know him better.

107
00:04:28,994 --> 00:04:31,096
It's rare to find someone like that.

108
00:04:31,163 --> 00:04:32,998
- Who can it be?
- She did say that.

109
00:04:33,065 --> 00:04:36,168
WHO IS THIS CAT-LIKE GIRL
WHO LIKES KEUN-SUK?

110
00:04:36,235 --> 00:04:37,402
DEEP IN THOUGHT

111
00:04:37,469 --> 00:04:39,872
- I have two candidates.
- Tell us about them.

112
00:04:39,938 --> 00:04:41,774
- Two people?
- Yes, I have two candidates.

113
00:04:41,840 --> 00:04:43,208
One is a non-celebrity

114
00:04:43,275 --> 00:04:44,877
and the other is an actor.

115
00:04:45,677 --> 00:04:46,678
- An actor?
- Yeah.

116
00:04:46,745 --> 00:04:47,913
THE GIRLS ARE INTRIGUED THIS TIME

117
00:04:47,980 --> 00:04:50,549
- My friend's a superstar.
- Who can it be?

118
00:04:50,616 --> 00:04:51,617
What's more

119
00:04:51,984 --> 00:04:52,985
he's handsome.

120
00:04:55,821 --> 00:04:57,523
UNABLE TO SUPPRESS A SMILE

121
00:04:57,589 --> 00:04:59,825
Is he like an A-lister?

122
00:05:00,125 --> 00:05:01,393
- He's an absolute A-lister.
- Really?

123
00:05:01,460 --> 00:05:02,494
A FELLOW SAME-AGE TOP STAR

124
00:05:02,561 --> 00:05:03,962
Is he available?

125
00:05:04,530 --> 00:05:05,597
It won't hurt to ask.

126
00:05:05,664 --> 00:05:07,132
- Yes, ask him.
- I'll do that.

127
00:05:07,733 --> 00:05:09,701
I'll ask if he's available.

128
00:05:10,602 --> 00:05:11,670
Who can it be?

129
00:05:12,704 --> 00:05:15,440
There's someone who comes to mind.

130
00:05:15,808 --> 00:05:16,875
- Who is it?
- Who is it?

131
00:05:17,876 --> 00:05:18,877
Well...

132
00:05:19,244 --> 00:05:20,345
He's practically my mini-me.

133
00:05:21,113 --> 00:05:22,314
- You?
- Your mini-me?

134
00:05:23,015 --> 00:05:25,317
He's my favorite mini-me.

135
00:05:25,384 --> 00:05:28,086
ANOTHER PRINCE IS MENTIONED

136
00:05:28,520 --> 00:05:30,222
- I have someone who comes to mind.
- Who can it be?

137
00:05:30,289 --> 00:05:31,990
It's someone in the elite class.

138
00:05:32,057 --> 00:05:33,725
- Highly intelligent.
- Really?

139
00:05:35,027 --> 00:05:36,295
This should be fun.

140
00:05:36,361 --> 00:05:38,163
It's really last-minute.

141
00:05:38,230 --> 00:05:40,232
I'd appreciate anyone who can come.

142
00:05:41,099 --> 00:05:43,202
Yeah, and if we could all be friends

143
00:05:43,268 --> 00:05:44,303
- it'd be so nice.
- Totally.

144
00:05:44,369 --> 00:05:46,371
IT WOULD BE NICE
IF WE ALL BECAME FRIENDS

145
00:05:46,438 --> 00:05:49,875
What if we throw a party

146
00:05:49,942 --> 00:05:52,845
but no one shows up,
and it's just the six of us again?

147
00:05:52,911 --> 00:05:54,213
- Just cricket sounds.
- Yeah.

148
00:05:54,279 --> 00:05:55,781
Cricket sounds like in animations.

149
00:05:56,148 --> 00:05:58,283
A small party can be nice,
rather than a wild one.

150
00:05:58,350 --> 00:06:00,352
- Tomorrow should be fun, right?
- You bet.

151
00:06:00,419 --> 00:06:01,687
Let's have a meaningful day.

152
00:06:02,521 --> 00:06:03,522
EXCITED

153
00:06:03,589 --> 00:06:05,891
WHO WILL END UP COMING?

154
00:06:06,625 --> 00:06:07,960
<i>What if no one shows up tomorrow?</i>

155
00:06:08,026 --> 00:06:09,194
<i>That'd make it funny.</i>

156
00:06:09,261 --> 00:06:11,864
<i>- What?</i>
<i>- That's fun in its own way.</i>

157
00:06:12,497 --> 00:06:15,267
NO ONE GETS ANY SLEEP
OUT OF ANXIETY AND EXCITEMENT

158
00:06:15,667 --> 00:06:19,137
EVERYONE IS BUSY
SENDING OUT INVITATIONS

159
00:06:19,938 --> 00:06:23,675
DESPERATELY HOPING
AT LEAST SOME WILL BE AVAILABLE

160
00:06:24,243 --> 00:06:26,111
THE NIGHT OF ANTICIPATION ENDS

161
00:06:26,178 --> 00:06:29,615
WHO WILL VISIT THE HOUSEMATES TODAY?

162
00:06:30,382 --> 00:06:33,685
THE 2ND-FLOOR HOUSEMATES
ARE STILL IN DREAMLAND

163
00:06:33,752 --> 00:06:35,787
CURLED UP

164
00:06:35,854 --> 00:06:39,358
THEY NOW SLEEP IN THE SAME POSITION

165
00:06:40,259 --> 00:06:44,263
THE 1ST-FLOOR HOUSEMATES
ARE ALSO STILL IN DREAMLAND

166
00:06:44,329 --> 00:06:47,399
SHIFTS

167
00:06:49,201 --> 00:06:52,070
DO-YEON RISES EARLY
DESPITE NOT HAVING WORK TODAY

168
00:06:53,372 --> 00:06:55,407
AS PER HER MORNING ROUTINE

169
00:06:55,474 --> 00:06:57,743
SHE'S PICKING UP HER PHONE?

170
00:06:58,210 --> 00:07:01,513
SHE USUALLY READS IN THE MORNING

171
00:07:02,080 --> 00:07:05,517
WHY IS SHE CHECKING HER PHONE TODAY?

172
00:07:06,518 --> 00:07:08,153
AS SOON AS SHE'S DONE

173
00:07:08,220 --> 00:07:11,390
SHE GETS OUT OF THE BED

174
00:07:12,691 --> 00:07:16,561
THIS INTROVERT USUALLY STAYS IN BED
FOR 2 HOURS TO AVOID HER HOUSEMATES

175
00:07:17,496 --> 00:07:19,398
SNEAKS OUT

176
00:07:19,464 --> 00:07:23,468
WHY IS SHE LEAVING HER BEDROOM
RIGHT AFTER WAKING UP?

177
00:07:24,770 --> 00:07:28,273
SHE'S HEADING STRAIGHT TO THE KITCHEN

178
00:07:29,007 --> 00:07:30,876
BUT DO-YEON IS HARDLY A GOOD COOK

179
00:07:30,943 --> 00:07:32,711
WHAT BRINGS HER HERE?

180
00:07:33,612 --> 00:07:36,148
OPENS THE FRIDGE

181
00:07:38,083 --> 00:07:41,586
SHE STARTS TAKING OUT INGREDIENTS

182
00:07:42,321 --> 00:07:45,324
WHAT HAS GOTTEN INTO
GUGI-DONG'S NEWBIE COOK?

183
00:07:45,390 --> 00:07:48,026
<i>Since it is our last day together</i>

184
00:07:48,093 --> 00:07:49,861
I wanted to cook for my housemates

185
00:07:50,362 --> 00:07:52,497
as a little present.

186
00:07:52,698 --> 00:07:53,765
She's clueless about cooking.

187
00:07:53,832 --> 00:07:54,866
DAY 1

188
00:07:55,867 --> 00:07:57,703
- I got a cut, too.
- Where?

189
00:07:58,003 --> 00:08:02,908
NEWBIE COOK IS BANNED
FROM THE KITCHEN AFTER THE INCIDENT

190
00:08:03,976 --> 00:08:08,280
DO-YEON HAS FELT BAD
FOR NOT HELPING OUT

191
00:08:09,514 --> 00:08:13,785
My housemates put so much effort
into preparing delicious meals.

192
00:08:13,852 --> 00:08:17,689
I wanted to do something in return.

193
00:08:17,756 --> 00:08:20,292
I was worried they might come
while I was still cooking.

194
00:08:20,359 --> 00:08:22,260
They could finish
everything in a flash.

195
00:08:22,327 --> 00:08:24,329
That would defeat the whole purpose.

196
00:08:24,396 --> 00:08:25,464
That's why I was worried.

197
00:08:26,765 --> 00:08:30,936
<i>It was a breakfast buffet theme</i>
<i>inspired by a hotel or B&amp;B.</i>

198
00:08:32,304 --> 00:08:34,573
SO NERVOUS

199
00:08:35,173 --> 00:08:37,976
THIS 14-YEAR DELIVERY FAN
RARELY PREPARES BREAKFAST FOR HERSELF

200
00:08:38,543 --> 00:08:40,312
CAN THIS NEWBIE COOK

201
00:08:40,379 --> 00:08:44,850
PREPARE BREAKFAST FOR 6 PEOPLE?

202
00:08:45,817 --> 00:08:48,053
CURRENT TIME

203
00:08:48,120 --> 00:08:50,589
HOW LONG WILL IT TAKE?

204
00:08:51,023 --> 00:08:55,060
FIRST DISH
ORANGES, A STAPLE IN BREAKFAST BUFFET

205
00:08:55,494 --> 00:08:57,062
IT IS ALMOST IMPOSSIBLE TO RUIN THIS

206
00:08:57,129 --> 00:08:58,697
ALL YOU NEED TO DO IS CUT THEM UP

207
00:08:59,197 --> 00:09:03,235
STARTS WASHING THE ORANGES

208
00:09:03,301 --> 00:09:05,904
ONE AT A TIME

209
00:09:06,705 --> 00:09:09,741
SLOWLY

210
00:09:09,808 --> 00:09:12,644
AND LEISURELY

211
00:09:13,078 --> 00:09:16,982
SHE TAKES TIME AND EFFORT
TO WASH THE ORANGES

212
00:09:18,316 --> 00:09:21,787
SHE IS IN NO WAY IN A RUSH

213
00:09:22,821 --> 00:09:24,890
WAIT, AM I DOING THIS RIGHT?

214
00:09:25,190 --> 00:09:26,925
I don't think this is how it looked.

215
00:09:26,992 --> 00:09:28,326
Do I keep the top part?

216
00:09:28,393 --> 00:09:29,828
WHEN WILL SHE EVER GET IT DONE?

217
00:09:29,895 --> 00:09:31,730
Darn it.

218
00:09:32,297 --> 00:09:34,499
I should've kept the top.

219
00:09:35,133 --> 00:09:36,802
What do I do?

220
00:09:36,868 --> 00:09:38,336
WHY ARE THE STICKERS STILL ON?

221
00:09:38,403 --> 00:09:39,538
Darn it.

222
00:09:39,604 --> 00:09:40,605
HOW IS SHE NOT NOTICING THEM?

223
00:09:40,672 --> 00:09:42,074
I have to hide these.

224
00:09:43,141 --> 00:09:44,142
All done.

225
00:09:44,209 --> 00:09:46,478
THINGS DON'T LOOK GOOD
FOR NEWBIE COOK'S BREAKFAST BUFFET

226
00:09:46,545 --> 00:09:47,946
Can you believe it?

227
00:09:48,814 --> 00:09:51,216
LOUD CLATTER

228
00:09:53,685 --> 00:09:55,854
SHIFTS

229
00:09:56,621 --> 00:10:00,792
WILL SHE BE ABLE TO GET READY
BEFORE EVERYONE GETS UP?

230
00:10:01,293 --> 00:10:02,294
Do I cut this part?

231
00:10:02,360 --> 00:10:03,361
ANOTHER BUFFET STAPLE, BANANAS

232
00:10:03,428 --> 00:10:04,596
I hope so.

233
00:10:06,231 --> 00:10:07,232
SOMEWHAT BOLDER

234
00:10:07,299 --> 00:10:08,467
I think they cut them like this.

235
00:10:09,901 --> 00:10:12,104
PILED UP

236
00:10:12,904 --> 00:10:15,407
A MOUND OF BANANAS

237
00:10:17,542 --> 00:10:20,412
WHY DOES IT LOOK FAMILIAR?

238
00:10:20,712 --> 00:10:22,280
I wasn't going for a zoo vibe.

239
00:10:22,948 --> 00:10:26,084
I started preparing raw food first.

240
00:10:26,585 --> 00:10:29,421
THIS ISN'T FOOD FOR ORANGUTANS

241
00:10:30,088 --> 00:10:32,057
DECIDING WHAT HUMAN FOOD TO MAKE NEXT

242
00:10:32,124 --> 00:10:33,492
Caprese...

243
00:10:34,960 --> 00:10:38,096
HER NEXT PROJECT IS CAPRESE,
A CLASSY BREAKFAST DISH

244
00:10:38,163 --> 00:10:39,731
30 MINUTES HAVE PASSED ALREADY

245
00:10:39,798 --> 00:10:41,733
Is it this way or like this?

246
00:10:42,267 --> 00:10:45,904
FIRST TIME MAKING CAPRESE
IN FORTY YEARS

247
00:10:47,305 --> 00:10:49,107
ONE CUT

248
00:10:49,174 --> 00:10:51,243
ONE PHOTO CHECK

249
00:10:51,843 --> 00:10:53,745
The key is getting thin slices.

250
00:10:53,812 --> 00:10:57,415
A QUICK CHECK AFTER EVERY SLICE

251
00:10:57,883 --> 00:11:01,319
SPEND 10 MINUTES CUTTING THE TOMATOES

252
00:11:02,387 --> 00:11:03,989
TIME TO ARRANGE
CHEESE AND TOMATO SLICES

253
00:11:04,055 --> 00:11:05,257
Cheese should be at the end.

254
00:11:07,459 --> 00:11:08,760
THIS PROCESS

255
00:11:08,827 --> 00:11:10,996
ALSO TAKES AGES

256
00:11:11,062 --> 00:11:13,131
CAN SHE REALLY MAKE A BUFFET FOR 6?

257
00:11:13,565 --> 00:11:14,733
Why does it look so off?

258
00:11:16,368 --> 00:11:19,237
SOMETHING IS MISSING

259
00:11:19,871 --> 00:11:23,074
WHAT'S THE MISSING ELEMENT?

260
00:11:23,775 --> 00:11:25,977
RIGHT INTO SEARCH MODE

261
00:11:26,044 --> 00:11:27,112
I got everything... Wait.

262
00:11:27,179 --> 00:11:28,947
BASIL LEAVES

263
00:11:30,348 --> 00:11:32,517
BUT

264
00:11:32,584 --> 00:11:33,652
Basil.

265
00:11:33,718 --> 00:11:36,121
SHE FORGOT TO ORDER BASIL

266
00:11:37,088 --> 00:11:39,124
CAN I USE ANY OTHER VEGETABLE?

267
00:11:40,225 --> 00:11:43,929
DO-YEON'S SUBSTITUTE CHOICE

268
00:11:43,995 --> 00:11:46,298
A BAG OF SPINACH?

269
00:11:46,364 --> 00:11:50,302
ONLY A NEWBIE COOK
WOULD MAKE SUCH A CHOICE

270
00:11:50,502 --> 00:11:54,739
CAN I EAT RAW SPINACH, THOUGH?

271
00:11:54,806 --> 00:11:56,708
IS IT SAFE TO EAT RAW SPINACH?

272
00:11:56,775 --> 00:11:58,977
A LARGE QUANTITY OF SPINACH
MAY INCREASE KIDNEY STONE RISKS

273
00:11:59,044 --> 00:12:00,545
GUESS THE ANSWER IS NO

274
00:12:02,380 --> 00:12:05,250
SPINACH IS OUT

275
00:12:05,317 --> 00:12:08,253
OTHER VEGETABLE TO THE RESCUE

276
00:12:09,120 --> 00:12:12,624
CONCERNED ABOUT PRESENTATION
DESPITE THE TIGHT SCHEDULE

277
00:12:13,358 --> 00:12:14,893
A SOMEWHAT GREEN CAPRESE

278
00:12:14,960 --> 00:12:16,461
Maybe I shouldn't cut these.

279
00:12:18,396 --> 00:12:21,233
ALL IT NEEDS NOW
IS THE BALSAMIC GLAZE

280
00:12:21,299 --> 00:12:23,301
It's surprisingly easy to make.

281
00:12:23,802 --> 00:12:25,570
BIG SPLASH

282
00:12:25,637 --> 00:12:28,173
A SEA OF BALSAMIC GLAZE

283
00:12:28,406 --> 00:12:30,508
That's too much.
I added too much, didn't I?

284
00:12:31,109 --> 00:12:34,613
WHO KNEW YOU COULD RUIN CAPRESE?

285
00:12:35,347 --> 00:12:36,681
I can pour some out.

286
00:12:38,016 --> 00:12:39,117
That should do it.

287
00:12:39,184 --> 00:12:40,952
QUICK DAMAGE CONTROL

288
00:12:41,019 --> 00:12:42,654
BARELY MADE IT

289
00:12:42,721 --> 00:12:43,722
Is this right?

290
00:12:44,089 --> 00:12:45,624
50 MINUTES HAVE PASSED ALREADY

291
00:12:45,690 --> 00:12:48,994
THE COMPLETED DISHES SO FAR

292
00:12:49,928 --> 00:12:52,464
It's giving <i>Midnight Diner </i>vibe.

293
00:12:52,530 --> 00:12:54,132
THIS DISH WILL FINALLY INVOLVE FIRE

294
00:12:54,199 --> 00:12:57,402
OCTOPUS-SHAPED SAUSAGES

295
00:12:58,036 --> 00:13:02,140
THIS HOTEL'S BUFFET PRIORITIZES
PRESENTABILITY OVER SPEED

296
00:13:02,707 --> 00:13:03,775
ALMOST MISSES

297
00:13:04,109 --> 00:13:06,745
IT TAKES 15 MINUTES TO CUT THEM

298
00:13:07,545 --> 00:13:08,580
It's so cute.

299
00:13:08,647 --> 00:13:10,048
IT TAKES 15 MINUTES TO GRILL THEM

300
00:13:11,549 --> 00:13:15,186
FINALLY READY AFTER 30 MINUTES

301
00:13:15,253 --> 00:13:17,422
IT'S NOT DONE YET

302
00:13:17,489 --> 00:13:18,490
CAUTIOUS

303
00:13:18,556 --> 00:13:19,724
Shoot.

304
00:13:21,826 --> 00:13:23,695
I meant to draw eyes with ketchup.

305
00:13:23,762 --> 00:13:25,730
TWO EYES ON EACH OCTOPUS?

306
00:13:27,032 --> 00:13:29,934
WITH A LOT OF CARE AND EFFORT

307
00:13:30,001 --> 00:13:33,471
SHE IS PLANTING THEM EYES

308
00:13:34,606 --> 00:13:36,207
Oh, no.

309
00:13:36,274 --> 00:13:37,709
THIS MIGHT BECOME A LUNCH BUFFET

310
00:13:38,109 --> 00:13:41,146
1 HOUR AND 30 MINUTES HAVE PASSED

311
00:13:41,746 --> 00:13:43,181
HER GOAL WAS OCTOPUS

312
00:13:43,248 --> 00:13:46,318
BUT THEY LOOK LIKE GHOSTS
SHEDDING BLOODY TEARS

313
00:13:46,985 --> 00:13:48,720
Let's try making a rolled omelet.

314
00:13:48,787 --> 00:13:50,789
If I fail, I'll make scrambled eggs.

315
00:13:51,990 --> 00:13:55,960
FIRST ROLLED OMELET IN 40 YEARS

316
00:13:57,762 --> 00:13:59,597
Is it 9:30 a.m. already?

317
00:13:59,664 --> 00:14:02,233
THE HOUSEMATES WILL BE UP SOON

318
00:14:02,634 --> 00:14:05,303
COOK A ROLLED OMELET
BEFORE EVERYONE GETS UP

319
00:14:05,804 --> 00:14:06,871
SCRAMBLING

320
00:14:06,938 --> 00:14:09,174
WHERE IS THE SPATULA?

321
00:14:10,141 --> 00:14:12,310
A RICE PADDLE
TO MAKE A ROLLED OMELET?

322
00:14:12,377 --> 00:14:13,445
This won't work.

323
00:14:14,245 --> 00:14:17,015
THINGS ALWAYS GO MISSING
WHEN YOU NEED THEM THE MOST

324
00:14:18,216 --> 00:14:20,485
NEW TOOL OBTAINED

325
00:14:22,287 --> 00:14:23,521
ACTUALLY, THAT'S ALSO A RICE PADDLE

326
00:14:23,588 --> 00:14:25,023
Can't I salvage this somehow?

327
00:14:25,357 --> 00:14:28,326
THE TASTE IS THE KEY, NOT THE LOOKS

328
00:14:30,762 --> 00:14:34,065
QUICKLY ADDS MORE BEATEN EGG
AND PREPARES TO ROLL IT

329
00:14:36,835 --> 00:14:40,004
DETERMINEDLY HOLDS
A SPATULA IN EACH HAND

330
00:14:43,308 --> 00:14:45,477
It worked.

331
00:14:45,543 --> 00:14:46,544
MADE IT TO THE HALF-WAY MARK

332
00:14:46,611 --> 00:14:47,679
I think I did it.

333
00:14:48,146 --> 00:14:49,781
I just need to flip it one more time.

334
00:14:49,848 --> 00:14:50,849
A BIT TOO WIDE, BUT IT'S FINE

335
00:14:51,750 --> 00:14:53,218
SUCCESS

336
00:14:54,185 --> 00:14:58,757
CONGRATS ON YOUR FIRST ROLLED OMELET

337
00:14:59,324 --> 00:15:01,192
I should be on <i>C***nary Class Wars.</i>

338
00:15:01,259 --> 00:15:02,460
GUGI-DONG'S WHITE SPOON CHEF

339
00:15:02,827 --> 00:15:04,028
I'm jazzed.

340
00:15:04,662 --> 00:15:05,797
SO THIS IS THE JOY IN COOKING

341
00:15:05,864 --> 00:15:07,599
This is wild. I did an amazing job.

342
00:15:07,799 --> 00:15:09,067
My goodness.

343
00:15:09,134 --> 00:15:10,668
MAKING IT PRESENTABLE
FOR THE HOUSEMATES' SAKE

344
00:15:10,735 --> 00:15:12,036
My gosh.

345
00:15:12,771 --> 00:15:14,472
What should I write?
A heart feels too corny.

346
00:15:14,539 --> 00:15:16,207
A MESSAGE DECORATION
DESPITE THE TIGHT SCHEDULE

347
00:15:16,274 --> 00:15:19,077
HYPER-FOCUSED MS. LONG-LEGS

348
00:15:20,578 --> 00:15:22,781
FRIENDSHIP

349
00:15:23,848 --> 00:15:25,016
I live for corny stuff.

350
00:15:25,083 --> 00:15:26,084
LITTLE HEART DECORATION

351
00:15:26,951 --> 00:15:28,219
Gosh, it's so corny.

352
00:15:28,286 --> 00:15:29,521
A LOT OF HEART AND TIME WENT INTO IT

353
00:15:29,587 --> 00:15:30,755
This is great.

354
00:15:30,822 --> 00:15:32,090
PROUD

355
00:15:32,891 --> 00:15:33,892
How exciting.

356
00:15:33,958 --> 00:15:35,894
RUSHES OVER TO SET THE TABLE
BEFORE ANYONE WAKES UP

357
00:15:40,098 --> 00:15:42,967
WHY IS DO-YEON IN THE KITCHEN?

358
00:15:43,034 --> 00:15:44,102
KEUN-SUK WOKE UP ALREADY?

359
00:15:44,169 --> 00:15:45,637
SWALLOWS HARD

360
00:15:46,571 --> 00:15:47,972
Can you go back upstairs for a bit?

361
00:15:48,039 --> 00:15:50,375
OBEDIENT

362
00:15:50,442 --> 00:15:51,943
DO-YEON IS COOKING?

363
00:15:52,010 --> 00:15:54,145
IS THIS A DREAM OR REAL LIFE?

364
00:15:55,580 --> 00:16:00,485
SOMEHOW ANXIOUS

365
00:16:01,019 --> 00:16:02,620
This too will pass.

366
00:16:03,121 --> 00:16:05,323
PLEASE...

367
00:16:05,390 --> 00:16:08,092
AFTER RUNNING INTO ONE HOUSEMATE

368
00:16:08,159 --> 00:16:10,328
DO-YEON FEELS THE HEAT!

369
00:16:10,395 --> 00:16:12,797
2 HOURS HAVE PASSED ALREADY

370
00:16:13,631 --> 00:16:15,733
<i>I need to hurry.</i>
<i>They'll all be up soon.</i>

371
00:16:17,035 --> 00:16:20,738
FOR A SUCCESSFUL SURPRISE EVENT,
SPEED IS A MUST!

372
00:16:25,543 --> 00:16:28,413
AM I DREAMING?

373
00:16:28,847 --> 00:16:31,716
WHY IS DO-YEON IN THE KITCHEN?

374
00:16:32,617 --> 00:16:33,618
Do-yeon.

375
00:16:36,921 --> 00:16:39,757
FREEZES

376
00:16:40,225 --> 00:16:42,994
THERE GOES THE SURPRISE EVENT

377
00:16:45,129 --> 00:16:46,898
DO YOU WANT ME TO LEAVE?

378
00:16:46,965 --> 00:16:48,800
YES, PLEASE

379
00:16:49,267 --> 00:16:52,570
CONCERNED, BUT RETREATS AS REQUESTED

380
00:16:53,171 --> 00:16:56,841
THE OTHER THREE ARE STILL ASLEEP

381
00:16:57,842 --> 00:17:00,178
SHE MUST WRAP THIS UP
BEFORE THEY GET UP

382
00:17:00,245 --> 00:17:01,346
Thank goodness.

383
00:17:01,846 --> 00:17:04,249
IN A RUSH

384
00:17:06,651 --> 00:17:07,919
What are you up to?

385
00:17:07,986 --> 00:17:09,721
THIRD PERSON TO WAKE UP

386
00:17:10,488 --> 00:17:11,890
- No!
- What?

387
00:17:12,223 --> 00:17:14,125
- What? I didn't see anything.
- Get back.

388
00:17:14,192 --> 00:17:15,193
Can I get some water?

389
00:17:15,260 --> 00:17:16,594
Pass me your cup.

390
00:17:17,295 --> 00:17:18,730
- What's going on?
- Keep your eyes closed.

391
00:17:18,796 --> 00:17:20,632
- Don't look.
- I didn't see anything.

392
00:17:20,698 --> 00:17:22,300
Go upstairs with your eyes covered.

393
00:17:22,367 --> 00:17:24,602
- Join me when I ask you to.
- Okay.

394
00:17:25,703 --> 00:17:27,171
I didn't see anything.

395
00:17:27,238 --> 00:17:28,506
Cover your eyes and your nostrils.

396
00:17:29,007 --> 00:17:32,644
By the table, in the second drawer...

397
00:17:32,710 --> 00:17:34,345
- On the right side
- Yes.

398
00:17:34,412 --> 00:17:35,980
- there are some eye drops.
- Eye drops?

399
00:17:36,047 --> 00:17:38,716
Eye drops and stick packs.

400
00:17:39,417 --> 00:17:40,418
I didn't see anything.

401
00:17:40,485 --> 00:17:41,486
RUNNING ERRANDS TO KEEP THE SECRET

402
00:17:41,553 --> 00:17:43,555
- Thanks, Do-yeon.
- Go upstairs. I'll call you later.

403
00:17:43,621 --> 00:17:44,622
Okay.

404
00:17:45,323 --> 00:17:46,858
She was cooking something.

405
00:17:46,925 --> 00:17:49,761
EVERYONE IS WORRIED

406
00:17:49,827 --> 00:17:50,828
What do I do?

407
00:17:50,895 --> 00:17:53,498
CHEF IS GETTING ANXIOUS

408
00:17:53,898 --> 00:17:55,700
RUSHES TO COOK HASH BROWNS

409
00:17:55,767 --> 00:17:57,735
BACON

410
00:17:57,802 --> 00:17:59,237
AND SAUSAGES

411
00:17:59,304 --> 00:18:03,141
DO-YEON'S HOTEL BUFFET
IS SOMEHOW COMING ALONG NICELY

412
00:18:03,207 --> 00:18:04,208
My gosh.

413
00:18:04,275 --> 00:18:08,479
RUSHES TO FINISH EVERYTHING
BEFORE EVERYONE WAKES UP

414
00:18:09,013 --> 00:18:12,016
THE BREAKFAST BUFFET
IS FINALLY READY AFTER 2.5 HOURS

415
00:18:12,517 --> 00:18:13,885
I should go wake them up.

416
00:18:13,952 --> 00:18:15,486
IT'S TIME TO BRING EVERYONE OVER

417
00:18:15,887 --> 00:18:17,522
SCURRIES

418
00:18:20,458 --> 00:18:21,459
Da-hee.

419
00:18:22,160 --> 00:18:23,328
Come have breakfast.

420
00:18:24,629 --> 00:18:26,664
IT'S HER FIRST TIME WAKING SOMEONE UP

421
00:18:26,731 --> 00:18:28,733
AFTER PREPARING BREAKFAST FOR THEM

422
00:18:29,634 --> 00:18:32,503
EXCITED ENOUGH
TO CLIMB 2 STAIRS AT ONCE

423
00:18:32,570 --> 00:18:35,239
OUT IN THE TERRACE

424
00:18:35,306 --> 00:18:36,774
COME ALONG

425
00:18:36,841 --> 00:18:38,710
What was that?

426
00:18:39,243 --> 00:18:40,878
- Come and eat.
- Eat?

427
00:18:40,945 --> 00:18:42,013
- Eat?
- I'm hungry.

428
00:18:42,380 --> 00:18:43,381
- That's insane.
- Eat?

429
00:18:43,448 --> 00:18:44,782
NICE ENOUGH TO FEIGN SURPRISE

430
00:18:44,849 --> 00:18:45,850
For real?

431
00:18:46,818 --> 00:18:48,519
Well, it's just breakfast.

432
00:18:48,586 --> 00:18:50,121
SLIGHTLY EMBARRASSED
BY THEIR REACTION

433
00:18:51,222 --> 00:18:53,558
- Come have breakfast, Daniel.
- Okay.

434
00:18:53,625 --> 00:18:55,093
- See you downstairs.
- All right.

435
00:18:55,159 --> 00:18:56,694
DID DO-YEON PREPARE BREAKFAST?

436
00:18:56,995 --> 00:19:00,498
AM I STILL DREAMING?

437
00:19:01,332 --> 00:19:04,402
ANXIETY DRIVES HER TO HURRY OVER

438
00:19:08,940 --> 00:19:11,409
DESPITE DA-HEE'S CONCERN

439
00:19:11,476 --> 00:19:14,679
QUITE A FEAST AWAITS HER

440
00:19:15,546 --> 00:19:19,117
ROUGH AROUND THE EDGES
BUT FILLED WITH GENUINE AFFECTION

441
00:19:19,183 --> 00:19:24,055
<i>Isn't this the best dish</i>
<i>Do-yeon can make on her own?</i>

442
00:19:24,122 --> 00:19:25,690
THE FIRST BREAKFAST DO-YEON MADE
FOR SOMEONE ELSE

443
00:19:25,757 --> 00:19:27,659
I can't believe this.

444
00:19:27,725 --> 00:19:29,260
TOUCHED

445
00:19:30,161 --> 00:19:32,296
GIGGLES

446
00:19:32,864 --> 00:19:36,000
NEWBIE COOK IS EMBARRASSED

447
00:19:36,467 --> 00:19:38,136
Join us for breakfast, Soo-jin.

448
00:19:38,202 --> 00:19:39,270
It's so hot.

449
00:19:39,871 --> 00:19:41,105
Hold on.

450
00:19:41,172 --> 00:19:43,207
WHAT IS GOING ON?

451
00:19:43,274 --> 00:19:44,342
Do-yeon.

452
00:19:44,409 --> 00:19:46,077
This is embarrassing.

453
00:19:46,144 --> 00:19:47,245
AM I STILL SLEEPING?

454
00:19:47,745 --> 00:19:48,913
EVERYONE GATHERS ONE BY ONE

455
00:19:48,980 --> 00:19:50,214
There are also flowers.

456
00:19:52,216 --> 00:19:53,418
What on earth?

457
00:19:53,484 --> 00:19:55,353
I PREPARED EVERYTHING

458
00:19:55,420 --> 00:19:57,021
- Daniel.
- What's going on?

459
00:19:57,088 --> 00:19:58,322
YOU PREPARED ALL THIS?

460
00:19:58,389 --> 00:20:00,124
This is incredible.

461
00:20:00,191 --> 00:20:02,460
MOVED BY DO-YEON'S COOKING ON HER OWN

462
00:20:02,527 --> 00:20:03,661
- Daniel.
- Just incredible.

463
00:20:03,728 --> 00:20:05,530
- My gosh.
- It feels like I'm abroad.

464
00:20:05,596 --> 00:20:06,798
It's giving hotel buffet vibes.

465
00:20:06,864 --> 00:20:07,865
Just a reminder.

466
00:20:07,932 --> 00:20:09,367
My inspo was a breakfast buffet

467
00:20:09,434 --> 00:20:11,536
so I'm wrapping up at 10:30 a.m.

468
00:20:11,602 --> 00:20:13,404
- I'd better eat quickly.
- We have ten minutes.

469
00:20:13,471 --> 00:20:14,939
Just ten minutes.

470
00:20:15,006 --> 00:20:17,175
That's when it ends.
I've been at this since 7:30 a.m.

471
00:20:17,241 --> 00:20:18,309
MIGHT BE HARD TO UNDERSTAND,
BUT IT TOOK FOREVER

472
00:20:18,376 --> 00:20:19,811
You've started preparing at 7:30 a.m.

473
00:20:19,877 --> 00:20:21,646
When did things come along?

474
00:20:21,713 --> 00:20:22,947
- Just now at 10 a.m.?
- At 10 a.m.

475
00:20:23,014 --> 00:20:24,015
I see.

476
00:20:24,515 --> 00:20:25,783
The owner gets the final call, right?

477
00:20:26,184 --> 00:20:27,385
Sorry.

478
00:20:27,452 --> 00:20:30,054
SOUNDS LIKE YOU WENT THROUGH A LOT

479
00:20:30,121 --> 00:20:31,122
- That's good.
- Are you sure?

480
00:20:31,189 --> 00:20:32,790
Since you prefer it mild...

481
00:20:32,857 --> 00:20:33,925
- That's right.
- You know what?

482
00:20:34,759 --> 00:20:35,760
Goodness.

483
00:20:35,827 --> 00:20:39,864
Look at what she's doing
to avoid cutting the ketchup letters.

484
00:20:39,931 --> 00:20:40,932
IT'S TOO PRECIOUS TO CUT

485
00:20:40,998 --> 00:20:42,166
Do-yeon.

486
00:20:42,233 --> 00:20:43,267
WAS I TOO OBVIOUS?

487
00:20:43,334 --> 00:20:45,269
You guys are free to cut them up.

488
00:20:46,137 --> 00:20:47,171
Thanks, Do-yeon.

489
00:20:47,238 --> 00:20:48,706
- No problem.
- Thank you for the food.

490
00:20:48,773 --> 00:20:50,608
- Thank you, Do-yeon.
- No worries. Please enjoy.

491
00:20:50,675 --> 00:20:52,276
- Thanks.
- You're the best.

492
00:20:52,343 --> 00:20:54,579
I HOPE THEY ENJOY EVERYTHING

493
00:20:54,645 --> 00:20:56,047
I should start with this.

494
00:20:56,114 --> 00:20:57,849
I WANT THE CAPRESE FIRST

495
00:20:57,915 --> 00:20:59,817
CURIOUS ABOUT HER REACTION

496
00:21:02,019 --> 00:21:04,422
It's nice having a mini buffet.

497
00:21:04,489 --> 00:21:05,656
This is so good.

498
00:21:06,491 --> 00:21:07,492
Delicious.

499
00:21:07,558 --> 00:21:08,993
HER FIRST COMPLIMENT ON HER COOKING

500
00:21:09,060 --> 00:21:10,528
It's delicious. This is so nice.

501
00:21:10,595 --> 00:21:13,030
A BIG BITE

502
00:21:13,865 --> 00:21:15,433
- It's ketchup.
- I drew eyes on them.

503
00:21:15,500 --> 00:21:16,567
They have ketchup eyes?

504
00:21:16,634 --> 00:21:17,769
Their eyes are drawn with ketchup.

505
00:21:17,835 --> 00:21:19,470
- Does this one have it?
- My gosh.

506
00:21:20,204 --> 00:21:23,908
- It's so cute.
- It probably took time cutting them.

507
00:21:23,975 --> 00:21:25,943
DO-YEON'S FIRST-EVER BUFFET
WON EVERYONE OVER

508
00:21:26,010 --> 00:21:27,211
It's delicious.

509
00:21:28,246 --> 00:21:29,514
I mean it.

510
00:21:29,580 --> 00:21:31,315
It was nothing.
