I know he's quite the foodie.

1250
00:48:36,296 --> 00:48:39,532
You said it was for a reservation
at some Japanese bar.

1251
00:48:42,001 --> 00:48:43,236
Before you got here

1252
00:48:43,303 --> 00:48:45,438
Do-yeon kept saying
she invited an actual cat.

1253
00:48:45,672 --> 00:48:48,875
- She got all of us pretty hyped up.
- Oh, right.

1254
00:48:48,942 --> 00:48:50,610
Meow.

1255
00:48:50,677 --> 00:48:51,778
- For real... Meow.
- Meow.

1256
00:48:52,378 --> 00:48:53,580
She's a shy cat.

1257
00:48:53,980 --> 00:48:55,081
AP IS DELIGHTED

1258
00:48:55,148 --> 00:48:56,549
Looks like you're shy, too.

1259
00:48:57,584 --> 00:48:58,952
She's a shy cat.

1260
00:48:59,018 --> 00:49:00,553
EMBARRASSED

1261
00:49:00,620 --> 00:49:02,956
- I hope you'll get closer.
- Thanks.

1262
00:49:03,022 --> 00:49:05,291
- I hope this takes up the full day.
- I love your attitude.

1263
00:49:05,558 --> 00:49:06,659
EVERYONE CRACKS UP

1264
00:49:06,726 --> 00:49:08,294
You live close by, don't you?

1265
00:49:08,361 --> 00:49:10,129
- Yes.
- Don't you have work tomorrow?

1266
00:49:10,563 --> 00:49:11,564
- No.
- No?

1267
00:49:11,631 --> 00:49:13,733
- What a coincidence.
- Just a plan for the evening.

1268
00:49:13,933 --> 00:49:16,069
I'll ask on behalf of people here

1269
00:49:16,135 --> 00:49:18,438
who want to know you better.

1270
00:49:18,504 --> 00:49:20,206
What kind of qualities
would they need?

1271
00:49:22,809 --> 00:49:24,310
They just need to...

1272
00:49:24,377 --> 00:49:26,145
To be honest,
I'd love to be friends with everyone.

1273
00:49:26,212 --> 00:49:27,614
My social circle's pretty small.

1274
00:49:29,182 --> 00:49:30,783
OH, NO

1275
00:49:31,084 --> 00:49:32,252
Really?

1276
00:49:32,318 --> 00:49:33,419
YOU POOR THING

1277
00:49:33,786 --> 00:49:35,922
Now that I've reached an age

1278
00:49:36,489 --> 00:49:39,192
where you rarely get
to meet new people.

1279
00:49:39,559 --> 00:49:42,562
So I find myself
doing whatever it takes

1280
00:49:42,629 --> 00:49:44,831
to seize all opportunities
to socialize.

1281
00:49:45,064 --> 00:49:47,200
I really want to, too.

1282
00:49:48,101 --> 00:49:49,802
It's really hard to make new friends.

1283
00:49:49,869 --> 00:49:51,604
I get it. As age goes by

1284
00:49:51,671 --> 00:49:54,240
we click better
with a different crowd, too.

1285
00:49:54,307 --> 00:49:56,276
- You're right.
- "As age goes by"?

1286
00:49:56,342 --> 00:49:58,344
As days go by... Hey!

1287
00:49:58,411 --> 00:49:59,545
SPOOKED

1288
00:49:59,612 --> 00:50:01,581
I'm the only one standing up here!

1289
00:50:02,215 --> 00:50:03,416
That can wear you out.

1290
00:50:03,483 --> 00:50:05,385
I'LL ZIP IT

1291
00:50:05,652 --> 00:50:10,256
THE MORE DO-YEON SHOUTS,
THE LESS AWKWARD IT GETS

1292
00:50:10,323 --> 00:50:12,225
Hong-gi and I are
the same on this end.

1293
00:50:12,292 --> 00:50:14,727
If you want to be close to Hong-gi

1294
00:50:14,794 --> 00:50:16,195
you've got to go a bit crazy.

1295
00:50:17,163 --> 00:50:20,033
IT'S NOT EASY TO MAKE NEW FRIENDS

1296
00:50:20,099 --> 00:50:23,970
Being rather atypical

1297
00:50:24,037 --> 00:50:26,806
there were times
when I felt rather alone.

1298
00:50:26,873 --> 00:50:28,641
But I'd like to remind you

1299
00:50:28,708 --> 00:50:30,410
that even I got to find
a kindred soul in Hong-gi.

1300
00:50:30,943 --> 00:50:32,412
You guys really look alike.

1301
00:50:32,478 --> 00:50:34,080
- Totally.
- Most definitely.

1302
00:50:34,147 --> 00:50:35,248
You do look alike.

1303
00:50:35,315 --> 00:50:36,949
THEY EVEN SIT THE SAME WAY

1304
00:50:37,016 --> 00:50:39,285
I wanted to prove
that I'm not all that odd.

1305
00:50:39,352 --> 00:50:40,887
We're not odd at all.

1306
00:50:40,953 --> 00:50:42,855
That's why I invited
someone who's exactly like me.

1307
00:50:42,922 --> 00:50:43,923
TWO PEAS IN A POD

1308
00:50:43,990 --> 00:50:45,558
- "We're not odd at all."
- Hong-gi.

1309
00:50:45,625 --> 00:50:47,593
- What's your MBTI?
- Well...

1310
00:50:47,660 --> 00:50:51,431
I get ENTP and ENFP 50-50.

1311
00:50:51,497 --> 00:50:52,598
So you're an ENTP.

1312
00:50:52,665 --> 00:50:53,900
I'm an ENTP, too.

1313
00:50:53,966 --> 00:50:56,069
I knew there was a reason
I felt close to you.

1314
00:50:56,135 --> 00:50:57,270
- I'm glad we've met.
- So cool.

1315
00:50:57,337 --> 00:50:58,504
Out of the blue...

1316
00:51:00,973 --> 00:51:03,176
- You rock.
- I really don't like that about him.

1317
00:51:03,242 --> 00:51:04,944
How absurd, right?

1318
00:51:05,011 --> 00:51:06,546
They actually have nothing in common.

1319
00:51:06,612 --> 00:51:07,613
None at all.

1320
00:51:07,680 --> 00:51:08,681
ALL HIS FRIENDS NAG AT HIM

1321
00:51:09,549 --> 00:51:10,817
Do you know my MBTI?

1322
00:51:11,651 --> 00:51:13,653
OOPS

1323
00:51:13,720 --> 00:51:14,721
You're an E...

1324
00:51:14,787 --> 00:51:15,955
He's guessing.

1325
00:51:16,022 --> 00:51:17,557
THAT MEANS HE DOESN'T KNOW

1326
00:51:18,224 --> 00:51:20,960
FAIL, AND OUR FRIENDSHIP IS OVER

1327
00:51:21,027 --> 00:51:22,328
E...

1328
00:51:22,895 --> 00:51:23,896
N...

1329
00:51:24,564 --> 00:51:25,565
F...

1330
00:51:27,233 --> 00:51:28,234
P?

1331
00:51:29,135 --> 00:51:30,269
He did get it right, but...

1332
00:51:30,336 --> 00:51:31,337
SAME REACTION

1333
00:51:31,404 --> 00:51:32,605
- He got it.
- True friends.

1334
00:51:33,039 --> 00:51:35,274
HE MANAGED TO SAVE THEIR FRIENDSHIP

1335
00:51:35,341 --> 00:51:36,342
GOOD JOB

1336
00:51:36,409 --> 00:51:38,444
I'm an introvert in the evening

1337
00:51:38,511 --> 00:51:39,512
and an extrovert by day.

1338
00:51:39,579 --> 00:51:41,647
- That's how I see it.
- Are you an extrovert now?

1339
00:51:41,714 --> 00:51:43,983
- Yes, I am.
- Okay.

1340
00:51:44,050 --> 00:51:46,586
Now, let's get closer
while we play the games.

1341
00:51:46,986 --> 00:51:48,654
- How are we going to get two teams?
- About that.

1342
00:51:48,721 --> 00:51:50,189
Most of us have our besties here

1343
00:51:50,256 --> 00:51:51,657
- but a few don't.
- Right.

1344
00:51:51,724 --> 00:51:53,626
- Soo-jin and Da-hee
- Yes.

1345
00:51:53,693 --> 00:51:55,695
can each take turns
to choose your teammates.

1346
00:51:55,762 --> 00:51:56,996
- We can choose people?
- Yes.

1347
00:51:57,497 --> 00:51:58,498
- To form a team?
- Yes.

1348
00:51:58,731 --> 00:52:00,366
I'll go with Daniel and So-min.

1349
00:52:00,600 --> 00:52:02,335
- Daniel and So-min.
- Thank you.

1350
00:52:02,402 --> 00:52:04,003
I'd like to have Gi-ru on my team.

1351
00:52:04,337 --> 00:52:06,406
- She then gets both of us.
- We'll be a team.

1352
00:52:06,639 --> 00:52:08,574
- Take me in as well.
- Okay.

1353
00:52:08,641 --> 00:52:10,209
- Is it because of me?
- Sure.

1354
00:52:10,276 --> 00:52:11,310
- Really?
- Is that why?

1355
00:52:11,377 --> 00:52:13,980
I WANT TO TEAM UP WITH MS. CAT-LIKE

1356
00:52:14,046 --> 00:52:16,048
<i>- So the five of us are a team.</i>
<i>- Exactly.</i>

1357
00:52:16,115 --> 00:52:17,950
<i>We're all sitting close by.</i>
<i>That's neat.</i>

1358
00:52:18,251 --> 00:52:19,819
<i>We're on the same team.</i>

1359
00:52:19,886 --> 00:52:20,887
<i>- All right.</i>
<i>- Okay.</i>

1360
00:52:20,953 --> 00:52:22,088
TEAM DA-HEE

1361
00:52:22,388 --> 00:52:24,624
Team Soo-jin gets the blue vest.

1362
00:52:24,690 --> 00:52:26,392
TEAM DA-HEE GETS THE RED VEST

1363
00:52:26,993 --> 00:52:28,795
Who got these vests? I'm curious.

1364
00:52:28,861 --> 00:52:30,430
- Daniel did.
- Your bestie did.

1365
00:52:30,496 --> 00:52:31,497
My bestie?

1366
00:52:31,564 --> 00:52:32,932
You have terrible taste.

1367
00:52:33,933 --> 00:52:34,934
Hey, bestie.

1368
00:52:35,001 --> 00:52:36,002
BITE ME

1369
00:52:36,068 --> 00:52:37,770
The first game is called

1370
00:52:37,837 --> 00:52:39,472
"Step On Me."

1371
00:52:39,539 --> 00:52:43,843
LET'S GET PHYSICAL TO BOND!
STEP ON ME

1372
00:52:44,243 --> 00:52:46,479
What a throwback. It's been a while.

1373
00:52:46,546 --> 00:52:49,449
- It's been ages since I tried this.
- It's been forever.

1374
00:52:49,515 --> 00:52:51,184
<i>Each team's player</i>

1375
00:52:51,250 --> 00:52:53,286
<i>will start hopping to the other side.</i>

1376
00:52:53,352 --> 00:52:54,854
<i>Upon contact,</i>
<i>they play rock-paper-scissors.</i>

1377
00:52:54,921 --> 00:52:56,889
<i>The winner can continue.</i>

1378
00:52:56,956 --> 00:52:58,024
EXPECT TO SEE A LOT OF CONTACT

1379
00:52:58,257 --> 00:53:01,294
The first to reach
the other team's territory

1380
00:53:01,360 --> 00:53:03,262
takes the match.

1381
00:53:03,463 --> 00:53:04,764
We can just shove people, right?

1382
00:53:04,831 --> 00:53:06,065
- Of course.
- With brute force?

1383
00:53:06,132 --> 00:53:07,300
Yes, we can do that.

1384
00:53:07,366 --> 00:53:08,968
- On contact, that is.
- I see.

1385
00:53:09,035 --> 00:53:10,369
I get the feeling shoving

1386
00:53:10,436 --> 00:53:11,771
is the way to victory.

1387
00:53:12,038 --> 00:53:14,140
SO COMFORTING AS AN ALLY

1388
00:53:14,207 --> 00:53:16,409
SO FRIGHTENING AS AN OPPONENT

1389
00:53:16,843 --> 00:53:18,778
It all comes down
to rock-paper-scissors.

1390
00:53:18,845 --> 00:53:19,846
Even if you start slow

1391
00:53:19,912 --> 00:53:21,647
- you can win if you're good at it.
- That's right.

1392
00:53:21,948 --> 00:53:24,150
MR. ELITE'S STRATEGY IS QUITE SIMPLE

1393
00:53:24,350 --> 00:53:25,685
What's the prize for this game?

1394
00:53:25,751 --> 00:53:26,786
All right, everyone.

1395
00:53:27,119 --> 00:53:28,521
The prize for this game

1396
00:53:28,588 --> 00:53:30,089
is assorted premium Korean pork.

1397
00:53:30,156 --> 00:53:31,257
Oh, that one?

1398
00:53:31,324 --> 00:53:33,593
THE MOST EXPENSIVE PRIZE,
ASSORTED PREMIUM KOREAN PORK

1399
00:53:33,659 --> 00:53:35,094
- Oh, that one?
- We've got to win.

1400
00:53:35,161 --> 00:53:37,196
- Let's go for it.
- Pork.

1401
00:53:37,463 --> 00:53:38,965
- Let's get everything.
- I'm in.

1402
00:53:39,365 --> 00:53:40,433
- Meat.
- Just say the word.

1403
00:53:40,500 --> 00:53:41,501
I'LL GET EVERYTHING

1404
00:53:41,567 --> 00:53:43,936
SWEET DA-HEE'S CHILLING AMBITION

1405
00:53:44,403 --> 00:53:46,305
PRIZE BRINGS EVERYONE TOGETHER

1406
00:53:46,372 --> 00:53:48,007
That's the real deal.

1407
00:53:48,541 --> 00:53:49,942
Is it our turn to step in?

1408
00:53:50,343 --> 00:53:52,178
Let's do our best, Gi-ru.

1409
00:53:53,145 --> 00:53:54,714
There it is.

1410
00:53:54,780 --> 00:53:56,382
PREOCCUPIED WITH PORK

1411
00:53:56,816 --> 00:54:00,586
- This is fresh premium pork.
- There are some ribs.

1412
00:54:00,653 --> 00:54:03,055
- We have an assorted variety here.
- Look at that cut.

1413
00:54:03,456 --> 00:54:05,758
It tastes heavenly with some salt.

1414
00:54:05,992 --> 00:54:07,960
- We're not going to grill it now.
- I know.

1415
00:54:08,027 --> 00:54:09,762
We've got skin-on and regular pork

1416
00:54:09,829 --> 00:54:10,897
- plus pork ribs.
- That's right.

1417
00:54:10,963 --> 00:54:12,698
- The skin is visible here.
- All right.

1418
00:54:12,765 --> 00:54:15,868
This fine Korean pork set
will go to the winning team.

1419
00:54:16,435 --> 00:54:18,037
MOOD LIGHTENED UP
THANKS TO THE PORK SET

1420
00:54:18,104 --> 00:54:19,105
All right.

1421
00:54:19,705 --> 00:54:21,507
- Why don't I go first?
- Go right ahead.

1422
00:54:21,574 --> 00:54:23,543
- It's a one-time match.
- We need a nimble player.

1423
00:54:23,609 --> 00:54:25,244
THE COMPETITION HAS TAKEN OVER,
LEAVING NO ROOM FOR AWKWARDNESS

1424
00:54:25,311 --> 00:54:26,913
Let's do this. It's time to go wild.

1425
00:54:26,979 --> 00:54:28,080
Ready.

1426
00:54:28,147 --> 00:54:29,815
Let's make that pork set ours.

1427
00:54:29,882 --> 00:54:30,983
HE NEEDS TO WIN TO WIN GI-RU OVER

1428
00:54:31,050 --> 00:54:32,251
This is for you, Gi-ru.

1429
00:54:32,318 --> 00:54:34,287
I LOVE KOREAN PORK

1430
00:54:34,353 --> 00:54:35,588
- I'll go first, Dae-ho.
- Okay.

1431
00:54:35,655 --> 00:54:36,722
I'll do it.

1432
00:54:37,456 --> 00:54:39,225
Let's do this.

1433
00:54:39,292 --> 00:54:40,526
- I'm on it.
- You've got this.

1434
00:54:40,593 --> 00:54:41,594
Jump right in.

1435
00:54:41,661 --> 00:54:42,728
I HAVE TO WIN
OR I'LL GET AN EARFUL FROM DA-HEE

1436
00:54:42,795 --> 00:54:44,030
Ready.

1437
00:54:44,630 --> 00:54:46,032
- Set. Go.
- Move fast.

1438
00:54:46,098 --> 00:54:48,000
- Looking good.
- No.

1439
00:54:48,067 --> 00:54:50,102
SUDDEN HUG

1440
00:54:50,436 --> 00:54:53,105
A BROMANCE PAIR NO ONE WAS EXPECTING

1441
00:54:53,172 --> 00:54:54,440
So you're an ENTP.

1442
00:54:54,507 --> 00:54:55,708
I'm an ENTP, too.

1443
00:54:56,008 --> 00:54:59,178
KID, WOULD YOU MIND IF I GOT CLOSER?

1444
00:55:00,279 --> 00:55:03,049
I'VE NEVER RUN INTO A GUY'S ARMS
ON OUR FIRST MEETING BEFORE

1445
00:55:03,115 --> 00:55:05,251
- Why the sudden shift to romance?
- What's going on?

1446
00:55:06,452 --> 00:55:09,221
- Rock-paper-scissors.
- Why the sudden shift to romance?

1447
00:55:09,288 --> 00:55:11,090
Rock-paper-scissors.

1448
00:55:11,157 --> 00:55:12,558
- I won!
- Darn it.

1449
00:55:12,625 --> 00:55:13,626
Quick, get out there.

1450
00:55:13,693 --> 00:55:14,694
HEARTTHROB HONG-GI WON

1451
00:55:15,761 --> 00:55:16,762
Quick, get out there.

1452
00:55:17,096 --> 00:55:18,397
- Hang in there.
- Oh, no.

1453
00:55:18,464 --> 00:55:20,099
THANK GOODNESS

1454
00:55:20,166 --> 00:55:22,001
- Rock-paper-scissors.
- Rock-paper-scissors.

1455
00:55:22,068 --> 00:55:23,135
DAE-HO AVOIDS CRISIS

1456
00:55:23,636 --> 00:55:25,471
Go, Dae-ho.

1457
00:55:25,538 --> 00:55:27,006
- Rock-paper-scissors.
- Rock-paper-scissors.

1458
00:55:27,273 --> 00:55:28,874
DAE-HO WON AGAIN!

1459
00:55:29,308 --> 00:55:31,243
- Go!
- You're doing great.

1460
00:55:31,544 --> 00:55:33,012
- Rock-paper-scissors.
- Rock-paper-scissors.

1461
00:55:33,079 --> 00:55:35,348
THAT'S 3 WINS IN A ROW!

1462
00:55:36,015 --> 00:55:39,251
HE ONLY NEEDS
TO DEFEAT DO-YEON TO WIN!

1463
00:55:48,555 --> 00:55:50,290
HAVE THEY GOTTEN THIS CLOSE ALREADY?

1464
00:55:50,357 --> 00:55:51,658
What happened?

1465
00:55:51,725 --> 00:55:53,760
UNEXPECTED COLLISION

1466
00:55:53,827 --> 00:55:55,996
SHOCKS EVERYONE

1467
00:55:56,696 --> 00:55:58,932
STARTLED BY THE BOLD ACTION
FROM THIS PAIR IN THEIR 40S

1468
00:56:00,267 --> 00:56:01,268
What just happened?

1469
00:56:01,334 --> 00:56:02,502
BEWILDERED BY THE SPICY ACTION

1470
00:56:03,770 --> 00:56:05,038
What was that?

1471
00:56:05,305 --> 00:56:07,207
Nothing happened.

1472
00:56:07,574 --> 00:56:09,242
EMBARRASSED

1473
00:56:10,343 --> 00:56:11,511
What's going on between you two?

1474
00:56:12,913 --> 00:56:15,248
Sorry, Do-yeon.
I'll apologize on his behalf.

1475
00:56:16,182 --> 00:56:17,350
Don't worry. It wasn't so bad.

1476
00:56:17,417 --> 00:56:18,919
- Really?
- My goodness.

1477
00:56:20,520 --> 00:56:21,521
Did they actually collide?

1478
00:56:21,588 --> 00:56:23,256
- Their cheeks touched slightly.
- Really?

1479
00:56:23,456 --> 00:56:24,991
- Move ahead, Do-yeon.
- Really?

1480
00:56:25,058 --> 00:56:26,226
We gave them a penalty.

1481
00:56:26,293 --> 00:56:27,294
One, two, three.

1482
00:56:27,627 --> 00:56:29,696
- Rock-paper-scissors.
- Rock-paper-scissors.

1483
00:56:29,763 --> 00:56:30,764
Come on. Move in.

1484
00:56:30,830 --> 00:56:31,831
ADVANCING AFTER A VICTORY

1485
00:56:32,232 --> 00:56:33,233
Oh, my.

1486
00:56:35,001 --> 00:56:37,604
ANOTHER UNEXPECTED COLLISION

1487
00:56:37,971 --> 00:56:40,073
CRACKING UP

1488
00:56:41,675 --> 00:56:44,244
I WAS JUST STANDING THERE

1489
00:56:44,811 --> 00:56:48,715
DO-YEON CAUSES ANOTHER CONTROVERSY

1490
00:56:48,782 --> 00:56:50,050
I mean...

1491
00:56:50,116 --> 00:56:52,085
She's a repeat offender.

1492
00:56:52,586 --> 00:56:54,988
- It was just...
- She keeps doing that.

1493
00:56:55,055 --> 00:56:56,056
I knew it.

1494
00:56:56,122 --> 00:56:58,091
HOW SPICY

1495
00:56:58,491 --> 00:57:00,360
You're way too enthusiastic.

1496
