there are more red panels.

1742
01:05:04,043 --> 01:05:06,312
- What a shame.
- So, Team Da-hee

1743
01:05:07,213 --> 01:05:08,214
takes the game!

1744
01:05:08,281 --> 01:05:10,383
VICTORY BUILT
AROUND COMPETITIVE GODDESS

1745
01:05:10,450 --> 01:05:12,251
Let's do this.

1746
01:05:12,318 --> 01:05:13,920
They're just not good enough.

1747
01:05:13,986 --> 01:05:15,254
FRIENDSHIP GROWS WITH VICTORY

1748
01:05:15,321 --> 01:05:17,590
Try to make it
more entertaining, will you?

1749
01:05:17,657 --> 01:05:19,725
Let's have some fun,
for goodness' sake.

1750
01:05:19,792 --> 01:05:21,360
It should be neck-and-neck.

1751
01:05:21,427 --> 01:05:22,428
I'm having a blast.

1752
01:05:22,495 --> 01:05:24,063
STRONGER FRIENDSHIP
BRINGS ON LOUDER VOICES

1753
01:05:24,330 --> 01:05:26,299
- We're giving it our all.
- It was fun, too.

1754
01:05:26,365 --> 01:05:27,400
Come on, admit it.

1755
01:05:27,467 --> 01:05:29,836
The way I see it,
the ham gave you tunnel vision.

1756
01:05:30,103 --> 01:05:32,038
You gave up on fairness
and sportsmanship.

1757
01:05:32,105 --> 01:05:34,474
I hope you're happy
you've won through cheating.

1758
01:05:34,540 --> 01:05:35,775
- Congrats.
- Thanks.

1759
01:05:35,842 --> 01:05:37,743
I'll give you the canned ham set.

1760
01:05:37,810 --> 01:05:39,212
Excuse me, MC.

1761
01:05:39,278 --> 01:05:40,413
That was really...

1762
01:05:41,147 --> 01:05:42,548
You went too far.

1763
01:05:43,249 --> 01:05:44,350
Seriously, that was low.

1764
01:05:44,784 --> 01:05:46,319
<i>Here's the truth.</i>

1765
01:05:46,385 --> 01:05:48,521
As you get older

1766
01:05:48,588 --> 01:05:51,724
making new friends becomes
closer to something of a miracle.

1767
01:05:52,458 --> 01:05:53,926
<i>The opportunities are rare</i>

1768
01:05:53,993 --> 01:05:55,828
<i>making it an extreme challenge.</i>

1769
01:05:55,895 --> 01:05:57,830
YOU FEEL MORE HESITANT
TO PUT YOURSELF OUT THERE

1770
01:05:57,897 --> 01:06:00,466
<i>It felt like we were</i>
<i>all innocent children again.</i>

1771
01:06:00,933 --> 01:06:02,768
<i>I had so much fun</i>
<i>and was truly happy.</i>

1772
01:06:02,835 --> 01:06:05,905
BONDING EASILY JUST AS THEY DID
IN THE PLAYGROUND AS CHILDREN

1773
01:06:05,972 --> 01:06:08,241
Let's do this!

1774
01:06:08,608 --> 01:06:10,076
SPECIAL TREAT
FROM THE YOUNGEST MEMBER

1775
01:06:10,143 --> 01:06:11,711
CLASSIC OLDIE, <i>LOVESICK</i>

1776
01:06:11,777 --> 01:06:13,913
EVERYONE SINGS ALONG
THE HIT SONG OF THEIR 20S

1777
01:06:18,784 --> 01:06:24,290
WHILE THE TIME HAS PASSED,
THE SONG STILL RESONATES WITH THEM

1778
01:06:25,892 --> 01:06:31,631
BECOMING ONE
THANKS TO THE CLASSIC SONG

1779
01:06:34,066 --> 01:06:39,839
HONG-GI'S SPECIAL GIFT SHINES
EVEN WITH A SIMPLE BLUETOOTH MIC

1780
01:06:42,375 --> 01:06:44,177
HE KILLED IT!

1781
01:06:44,243 --> 01:06:45,978
MY FRIEND ROCKS

1782
01:06:46,045 --> 01:06:47,713
- That was the best.
- So incredible.

1783
01:06:47,780 --> 01:06:49,882
OUR NEW FRIEND IS SO COOL

1784
01:06:49,949 --> 01:06:50,950
Thank you.

1785
01:06:51,017 --> 01:06:52,318
- It's an honor to be here.
- So cool.

1786
01:06:52,385 --> 01:06:54,287
- That's my pal, okay?
- He's so cool.

1787
01:06:54,487 --> 01:06:55,922
- Totally.
- So sick.

1788
01:06:55,988 --> 01:06:57,423
LET'S BE GOOD FRIENDS!

1789
01:06:58,424 --> 01:07:00,326
- Bye.
- Don't forget your presents.

1790
01:07:00,393 --> 01:07:01,527
Take them with you.

1791
01:07:01,594 --> 01:07:03,596
- Can I get your number?
- Oh, you want it?

1792
01:07:04,096 --> 01:07:06,933
- I hope this is not a fake number.
- No way.

1793
01:07:07,333 --> 01:07:08,868
PRIM

1794
01:07:08,935 --> 01:07:11,370
- Can we exchange numbers?
- For real? What's with you guys?

1795
01:07:11,437 --> 01:07:14,207
Hey, Do-yeon.
These guys are asking for my number.

1796
01:07:14,974 --> 01:07:16,142
- I just...
- I got the text.

1797
01:07:16,209 --> 01:07:18,144
- You did? Let me double-check.
- Sure.

1798
01:07:18,678 --> 01:07:20,513
CHUCKLES

1799
01:07:20,580 --> 01:07:22,648
- Not your second number, is it?
- Oh, no.

1800
01:07:22,715 --> 01:07:23,749
- "Second number"?
- No way.

1801
01:07:23,816 --> 01:07:26,085
People keep giving me
their second number.

1802
01:07:26,152 --> 01:07:27,420
Don't worry. I only keep one phone.

1803
01:07:27,486 --> 01:07:28,621
It's all in your head.

1804
01:07:28,955 --> 01:07:32,391
Do-yeon, if you're interested,
I'll give you the guys' number later.

1805
01:07:32,758 --> 01:07:33,759
Okay, thanks.

1806
01:07:33,826 --> 01:07:35,695
- You'll bring me closer to them.
- Really?

1807
01:07:35,761 --> 01:07:37,129
Could we exchange numbers, too?

1808
01:07:37,196 --> 01:07:39,232
Just a second, please.
Let me save this first.

1809
01:07:39,298 --> 01:07:40,399
Her phone's out of storage.

1810
01:07:40,466 --> 01:07:41,601
GENTLEMEN FIRST

1811
01:07:41,667 --> 01:07:43,769
<i>- I'll text you, Jae-hyeon.</i>
<i>- Would you like canned ham, Gi-ru?</i>

1812
01:07:43,836 --> 01:07:45,538
<i>Why are you flirting with me?</i>

1813
01:07:46,372 --> 01:07:48,074
- It's gotten so cold.
- Great work, Dae-ho.

1814
01:07:48,140 --> 01:07:49,642
- You too, guys.
- Good job, Dae-ho.

1815
01:07:49,709 --> 01:07:50,977
You guys must've had a lot of fun.

1816
01:07:51,444 --> 01:07:52,511
- Of course.
- Us? We sure did.

1817
01:07:52,578 --> 01:07:53,579
I had a blast.

1818
01:07:53,646 --> 01:07:55,147
It's always fun with a crowd.

1819
01:07:55,214 --> 01:07:57,650
- We're only two years apart.
- Exactly.

1820
01:07:57,717 --> 01:07:58,985
Good work, Hong-gi.

1821
01:07:59,051 --> 01:08:01,487
- You too.
- Thank you for the good time.

1822
01:08:01,554 --> 01:08:02,688
- Great work.
- You too.

1823
01:08:02,755 --> 01:08:03,923
You seemed to enjoy it the most.

1824
01:08:03,990 --> 01:08:05,258
Oh, well...

1825
01:08:05,992 --> 01:08:07,627
Around my age

1826
01:08:07,693 --> 01:08:09,395
it's hard to find people
to hang out with.

1827
01:08:09,462 --> 01:08:11,197
- Reach out to her first, Jae-hyeon.
- Of course.

1828
01:08:11,264 --> 01:08:12,531
MAY TODAY'S FRIENDSHIP GROW FURTHER

1829
01:08:12,598 --> 01:08:13,733
I'll call Gi-ru.

1830
01:08:14,133 --> 01:08:16,102
- "Where are you?"
- "This is Jae-hyeon."

1831
01:08:16,168 --> 01:08:17,903
- Thank you.
- Let's grab rice wine later, Dae-ho.

1832
01:08:17,970 --> 01:08:18,971
PROMISING TO MEET AGAIN

1833
01:08:19,038 --> 01:08:20,072
- Take care.
- See you.

1834
01:08:20,139 --> 01:08:21,140
LET'S FOCUS ON OUR GROUP NOW

1835
01:08:21,207 --> 01:08:22,208
<i>That was fun.</i>

1836
01:08:23,342 --> 01:08:25,144
A SMALL GATHERING
AFTER THE GUESTS LEFT

1837
01:08:25,211 --> 01:08:26,445
SIGHS

1838
01:08:26,512 --> 01:08:27,847
I feel hollow for some reason.

1839
01:08:28,681 --> 01:08:30,349
- Tell me about it.
- You keep sighing, right?

1840
01:08:30,416 --> 01:08:33,152
- Yeah.
- You can't help it for some reason.

1841
01:08:33,219 --> 01:08:34,587
THIS IS THEIR LAST DAY TOGETHER

1842
01:08:34,654 --> 01:08:37,356
AND THEY HAVE BEEN TRYING
TO IGNORE THAT ELEPHANT IN THE ROOM

1843
01:08:37,823 --> 01:08:40,559
3 HOURS UNTIL THEIR LEASE EXPIRES

1844
01:08:40,626 --> 01:08:41,861
AND THEY RETURN TO SOLITUDE

1845
01:08:41,927 --> 01:08:43,296
Aren't you guys hungry?

1846
01:08:43,362 --> 01:08:44,964
- Shall we get some snacks?
- Let's do

1847
01:08:45,031 --> 01:08:46,465
one more thing together
before we leave.

1848
01:08:47,033 --> 01:08:48,134
Let's eat together.

1849
01:08:48,200 --> 01:08:49,502
- One last time.
- One last time?

1850
01:08:49,568 --> 01:08:52,305
We didn't finish
the seasoned vegetables we bought.

1851
01:08:52,371 --> 01:08:54,240
- We can empty the fridge.
- We should.

1852
01:08:54,307 --> 01:08:55,441
- The fridge?
- We should.

1853
01:08:55,508 --> 01:08:56,776
We can make bibimbap.

1854
01:08:56,842 --> 01:08:58,778
- Hey.
- With everything in a bowl.

1855
01:08:58,844 --> 01:09:00,613
- Mix it all in one giant bowl.
- Yes.

1856
01:09:00,680 --> 01:09:01,747
- Yes.
- Bibimbap sounds nice.

1857
01:09:01,814 --> 01:09:03,082
Let's get aggressive, shall we?

1858
01:09:03,149 --> 01:09:04,750
- With fried eggs.
- Let's do this.

1859
01:09:04,817 --> 01:09:05,918
Are you adding the octopus, too?

1860
01:09:05,985 --> 01:09:08,087
- We're saying goodbye to it.
- That's a no, then.

1861
01:09:08,287 --> 01:09:09,488
It went to meet its maker.

1862
01:09:09,555 --> 01:09:10,656
ENTERS WITH NEW DETERMINATIONS

1863
01:09:10,723 --> 01:09:11,824
Let me check the side dishes.

1864
01:09:11,891 --> 01:09:12,958
CHEFS SOO-JIN AND KEUN-SUK

1865
01:09:13,025 --> 01:09:14,193
Bean sprouts.

1866
01:09:15,227 --> 01:09:16,962
- What else?
- Radish salad.

1867
01:09:17,029 --> 01:09:18,397
- Bracken.
- That's perfect.

1868
01:09:18,464 --> 01:09:19,665
We've got to have that bibimbap.

1869
01:09:19,732 --> 01:09:21,133
- Let's get to work.
- All right.

1870
01:09:21,200 --> 01:09:22,635
It's as good as decided.

1871
01:09:22,935 --> 01:09:25,104
- Let's mix them up.
- The heavens want us to do that.

1872
01:09:26,072 --> 01:09:27,340
Let's do this.

1873
01:09:27,406 --> 01:09:28,441
- Let's go!
- All right!

1874
01:09:28,507 --> 01:09:30,076
TA-DA

1875
01:09:30,142 --> 01:09:32,078
I'll cook six eggs for six of us.

1876
01:09:32,144 --> 01:09:33,145
Go ahead.

1877
01:09:33,212 --> 01:09:35,214
- It has significance.
- Of course.

1878
01:09:38,984 --> 01:09:40,152
Are we using all the side dishes?

1879
01:09:40,553 --> 01:09:41,554
Yes.

1880
01:09:42,655 --> 01:09:44,457
- We've got to add sesame oil.
- Of course.

1881
01:09:44,523 --> 01:09:46,092
INGREDIENTS BECOME ONE
JUST LIKE THE HOUSEMATES

1882
01:09:46,158 --> 01:09:47,226
- Should I add eggs now?
- Yeah.

1883
01:09:47,293 --> 01:09:48,294
Here we go.

1884
01:09:48,361 --> 01:09:49,795
WITH 6 FRIED EGGS ON TOP

1885
01:09:49,862 --> 01:09:52,898
6-PEOPLE-6-INGREDIENTS BIBIMBAP
IS READY NOW

1886
01:09:52,965 --> 01:09:54,433
- Let's do the mixing over there.
- Shall we?

1887
01:09:54,500 --> 01:09:56,035
- Can we do that?
- Let's mix it together.

1888
01:09:56,102 --> 01:09:57,737
- Let's do it together.
- Okay.

1889
01:09:57,803 --> 01:09:59,372
- Just one.
- Okay, then.

1890
01:09:59,438 --> 01:10:01,640
2 HOURS UNTIL THEY RETURN TO SOLITUDE

1891
01:10:01,707 --> 01:10:02,742
We're all set.

1892
01:10:02,975 --> 01:10:05,644
ONE LAST MEAL IN GUGI-DONG

1893
01:10:05,711 --> 01:10:07,847
- Pretty impressive.
- This looks nice.

1894
01:10:08,147 --> 01:10:09,382
- Shall we?
- Let's mix it up.

1895
01:10:09,448 --> 01:10:10,783
- Can we?
- Let's get to work!

1896
01:10:10,850 --> 01:10:13,018
BRINGING THE ENERGY UP
TO HIDE THEIR SADNESS

1897
01:10:14,086 --> 01:10:15,588
It's a gourmet meal
for a leftover cleanup.

1898
01:10:15,654 --> 01:10:17,022
- Totally.
- Absolutely.

1899
01:10:17,523 --> 01:10:18,791
Just like us, right?

1900
01:10:19,425 --> 01:10:20,826
- They're becoming one.
- Blending in.

1901
01:10:20,893 --> 01:10:22,128
Yes, everything came together.

1902
01:10:22,194 --> 01:10:23,295
Who's the rice?

1903
01:10:23,562 --> 01:10:24,930
It's a great dish

1904
01:10:24,997 --> 01:10:26,332
but you rarely make it
when you're alone.

1905
01:10:26,399 --> 01:10:27,767
- You get too many portions.
- Exactly.

1906
01:10:27,833 --> 01:10:30,569
- You want to add many side dishes.
- You're right.

1907
01:10:30,836 --> 01:10:33,172
It even tastes different
when you eat off a large bowl

1908
01:10:33,239 --> 01:10:34,507
- rather than a small bowl.
- Totally.

1909
01:10:34,707 --> 01:10:35,708
So true.

1910
01:10:36,442 --> 01:10:37,643
We've got no clumps.

1911
01:10:37,710 --> 01:10:39,712
SOMEHOW GETS EMOTIONAL
WHILE TALKING ABOUT BIBIMBAP

1912
01:10:39,779 --> 01:10:41,046
You're doing great, Soo-jin.

1913
01:10:41,113 --> 01:10:42,782
- She's so thorough.
- Good job.

1914
01:10:42,848 --> 01:10:43,983
Not a single white clump in sight.

1915
01:10:44,049 --> 01:10:46,051
- That's how it should be, right?
- It's amazing.

1916
01:10:46,786 --> 01:10:48,220
The vest makes you look

1917
01:10:48,287 --> 01:10:49,622
like a restaurant employee.

1918
01:10:50,556 --> 01:10:52,024
NOT MISSING THE CHANCE
TO MAKE A SILLY JOKE

1919
01:10:52,091 --> 01:10:53,826
- No doubt the food will be amazing.
- For sure.

1920
01:10:53,893 --> 01:10:55,261
It just has to be.

1921
01:10:55,327 --> 01:10:56,328
You did such a fine job.

1922
01:10:56,395 --> 01:10:58,063
- All right.
- It's more than ready to serve.

1923
01:10:58,130 --> 01:10:59,465
- All right.
- Bon appétit.

1924
01:10:59,532 --> 01:11:01,700
- Bon appétit.
- Bon appétit.

1925
01:11:02,802 --> 01:11:05,471
Turns out we didn't need fried eggs.
The egg soup is really nice.

1926
01:11:05,538 --> 01:11:07,540
- Your egg soup is amazing, Keun-suk.
- Is it good?

1927
01:11:07,606 --> 01:11:09,275
CHUCKLES

1928
01:11:09,608 --> 01:11:11,177
Dude, it's to die for.

1929
01:11:11,577 --> 01:11:13,179
- Is it the best?
- It's a killer. Try it.

1930
01:11:13,612 --> 01:11:14,680
All right.

1931
01:11:14,747 --> 01:11:17,583
- Take your favorite ingredients.
- Yes, we can do that.

1932
01:11:18,083 --> 01:11:22,021
THAT HITS THE SPOT

1933
01:11:22,321 --> 01:11:23,956
It's the full package.

1934
01:11:24,290 --> 01:11:25,825
I haven't heard that in a while.

1935
01:11:25,891 --> 01:11:29,595
SINGLE HARMONIOUS DISH
MADE UP WITH 6 SEASONED VEGETABLES

1936
01:11:29,662 --> 01:11:30,963
It's so good.

1937
01:11:31,030 --> 01:11:32,898
All the ingredients
come together nicely.

1938
01:11:32,965 --> 01:11:35,434
- Everything we had here was amazing.
- What?

1939
01:11:35,501 --> 01:11:36,735
All the dishes tasted amazing.

1940
01:11:36,802 --> 01:11:38,170
It's seasoned to perfection.

1941
01:11:39,672 --> 01:11:40,739
It's so good.

1942
01:11:43,342 --> 01:11:47,046
SILENCE FALLS

1943
01:11:47,112 --> 01:11:49,949
THEY HAVE NEVER BEEN THIS QUIET
DURING MEALTIME

1944
01:11:53,252 --> 01:11:57,656
DA-HEE KEEPS GLANCING OVER
AT THE LIVING ROOM

1945
01:11:59,692 --> 01:12:01,026
So this is our last meal together.

1946
01:12:01,093 --> 01:12:02,294
It makes you emotional, right?

1947
01:12:03,996 --> 01:12:05,164
It's just not sinking in.

1948
01:12:10,469 --> 01:12:12,238
Did you guys complete your card?

1949
01:12:13,038 --> 01:12:14,306
- Yeah.
- I did.

1950
01:12:15,341 --> 01:12:17,343
EARLIER, AFTER SEEING THE GUESTS OFF

1951
01:12:17,409 --> 01:12:18,577
What's this?

1952
01:12:18,644 --> 01:12:21,614
SOMETHING IS ON HIS BED

1953
01:12:27,152 --> 01:12:28,153
What is this?

1954
01:12:31,624 --> 01:12:33,893
"Your lease is up.

1955
01:12:34,260 --> 01:12:37,796
Please pack up your belongings
and vacate the room by midnight."

1956
01:12:38,497 --> 01:12:41,033
MOMENTS WHEN I WAS HAPPY
TO HAVE HOUSEMATES

1957
01:12:41,100 --> 01:12:43,536
MOMENTS WHEN I WAS DISTRESSED
TO HAVE HOUSEMATES

1958
01:12:43,602 --> 01:12:47,506
"Lastly, please write a comment
for each housemate."

1959
01:12:49,441 --> 01:12:51,844
THEY CAREFULLY WROTE DOWN

1960
01:12:51,911 --> 01:12:56,649
ALL THE THINGS THEY DIDN'T GET TO SAY

1961
01:12:59,752 --> 01:13:04,356
SOME WERE OVERCOME WITH EMOTIONS
AND HAD TO COMPOSE THEMSELVES

1962
01:13:05,891 --> 01:13:13,899
THEY MADE PREPARATIONS
TO RETURN TO THEIR SOLITARY LIVES

1963
01:13:15,100 --> 01:13:16,569
It feels like our first day, right?

1964
01:13:17,570 --> 01:13:19,672
- My thought exactly.
- We're chatting, sure.

1965
01:13:19,738 --> 01:13:21,574
- But we're just being vague.
- Yeah.

1966
01:13:23,509 --> 01:13:25,010
Knowing this is the end

1967
01:13:25,210 --> 01:13:27,546
makes you look back
on our time together.

1968
01:13:31,283 --> 01:13:33,852
SILENCE CONTINUES

1969
01:13:34,787 --> 01:13:36,088
SNORTS OUT A LAUGH

1970
01:13:36,522 --> 01:13:38,557
GRINS

1971
01:13:39,058 --> 01:13:41,393
WHAT'S WITH THIS STRANGE AIR?

1972
01:13:41,927 --> 01:13:43,596
- Let's come up with something.
- Okay.

1973
01:13:43,662 --> 01:13:45,631
No one's talking.

1974
01:13:46,231 --> 01:13:47,866
Why do our conversations
keep fizzling out?

1975
01:13:47,933 --> 01:13:50,836
Am I the only person who finds this
worse than our first day?

1976
01:13:51,036 --> 01:13:52,538
- No, I'm with you there.
- Right?

1977
01:13:53,105 --> 01:13:54,239
We all get it.

1978
01:13:54,306 --> 01:13:56,141
But if we really dig into it

1979
01:13:56,342 --> 01:13:57,810
I will get emotional...

1980
01:13:57,876 --> 01:13:59,712
That's why I don't want to.

1981
01:13:59,778 --> 01:14:01,513
- I see.
- When one person gets touchy-feely

1982
01:14:01,580 --> 01:14:03,482
- it will spread to the whole group.
- Okay.

1983
01:14:03,549 --> 01:14:05,584
I'm sure we're all faking a smile
to avoid that.

1984
01:14:05,651 --> 01:14:07,019
TEAM FORTIES WANTS TO REMAIN CALM

1985
01:14:07,987 --> 01:14:09,788
So we're all on the same page.

1986
01:14:11,757 --> 01:14:13,192
What will it feel like
when we get home?

1987
01:14:13,258 --> 01:14:14,259
I'm wondering that, too.

1988
01:14:14,927 --> 01:14:16,996
The moment I lie on my couch

1989
01:14:17,062 --> 01:14:19,098
the silence around me
will feel so strange.

1990
01:14:20,566 --> 01:14:24,570
<i>I've gotten used to hearing,</i>
<i>"Let's eat. What are you doing?"</i>

1991
01:14:24,637 --> 01:14:27,740
HOUSEMATES FILLED THE LIVING ROOM
WITH LIVELINESS

1992
01:14:27,806 --> 01:14:29,208
I'd be surrounded by silence.

1993
01:14:29,274 --> 01:14:32,378
THE SILENCE AT THEIR OWN HOMES
WILL FEEL MORE DEAFENING

1994
01:14:32,678 --> 01:14:35,781
I might not feel at home
in my own home. You feel me, right?

1995
01:14:35,848 --> 01:14:37,282
Totally. It will feel unfamiliar.

1996
01:14:37,349 --> 01:14:38,450
Even in my own home.

1997
01:14:39,385 --> 01:14:41,320
When I was packing my stuff

1998
01:14:41,387 --> 01:14:43,288
I could just do it
without getting emotional.

1999
01:14:43,355 --> 01:14:44,790
When I looked up

2000
01:14:44,857 --> 01:14:47,126
I saw Da-hee taking her suitcase out.

2001
01:14:47,192 --> 01:14:48,661
Man, that really shook me up.

2002
01:14:49,328 --> 01:14:51,797
DO-YEON WAS RESTING
AFTER PACKING HER BELONGINGS

2003
01:14:51,864 --> 01:14:55,901
THEN, SHE SAW DA-HEE
CARRYING HER SUITCASE

2004
01:14:57,503 --> 01:15:02,708
THEY UNDERSTOOD EACH OTHER
THROUGH THAT ONE LOOK

2005
01:15:03,742 --> 01:15:06,345
She had her suitcase in her arms,
and our eyes met.

2006
01:15:06,412 --> 01:15:08,280
That's when it hit me.
"She's leaving.

2007
01:15:08,347 --> 01:15:09,648
I'm leaving, too.

2008
01:15:09,715 --> 01:15:11,250
We won't be roommates anymore."

2009
01:15:11,316 --> 01:15:12,985
It felt so strange.

2010
01:15:14,253 --> 01:15:16,522
"We won't be roommates anymore"?
What are you implying?

2011
01:15:16,588 --> 01:15:17,856
How else do I put it?

2012
01:15:18,924 --> 01:15:20,225
Just eat your bibimbap.

2013
01:15:20,659 --> 01:15:23,462
Let's get it out of our system
before we leave.

2014
01:15:23,529 --> 01:15:26,031
- Let's do it.
- All right.

2015
01:15:26,498 --> 01:15:27,833
Sure, we might as well cut ties.

2016
01:15:27,900 --> 01:15:29,435
- All right.
- Good idea.

2017
01:15:29,501 --> 01:15:30,569
We won't miss each other then.

2018
01:15:31,136 --> 01:15:32,705
It's worse to leave things unclear.

2019
01:15:34,006 --> 01:15:36,875
When you phrase it that way,
we might have to go at it.

2020
01:15:36,942 --> 01:15:38,877
IF GUGI-DONG'S AHN-GEL
FEELS THAT WAY...

2021
01:15:38,944 --> 01:15:41,046
- Did you prepare a speech?
- Are you holding a grudge?

2022
01:15:41,380 --> 01:15:42,781
If Jae-hyeon demands it,
we have to do it.

2023
01:15:42,848 --> 01:15:43,882
- Of course.
- Oh, no.

2024
01:15:43,949 --> 01:15:45,250
- He meant it.
- I felt it, too.

2025
01:15:45,984 --> 01:15:47,653
<i>Want to read the cards together?</i>

2026
01:15:47,720 --> 01:15:48,987
<i>Okay, let's go get them.</i>

2027
01:15:50,355 --> 01:15:53,092
1 HOUR UNTIL THEY RETURN TO SOLITUDE

2028
01:15:53,158 --> 01:15:55,160
CLEARS THROAT

2029
01:15:56,095 --> 01:15:57,096
REACHES OUT

2030
01:15:57,162 --> 01:15:59,364
IRONCLAD DEFENSE

2031
01:15:59,932 --> 01:16:01,500
GRINS

2032
01:16:01,567 --> 01:16:02,568
This is hilarious.

2033
01:16:02,634 --> 01:16:03,969
We're keeping the cards covered

2034
01:16:04,036 --> 01:16:05,170
- to keep them secret.
- Yeah.

2035
01:16:05,237 --> 01:16:06,371
Everyone's feeling shy.

2036
01:16:06,939 --> 01:16:07,940
So shy.

2037
01:16:08,006 --> 01:16:09,341
EMBARRASSED TO GO OVER
THE CARDS TOGETHER

2038
01:16:09,408 --> 01:16:11,310
Let's make necessary changes
as we go along.

2039
01:16:11,643 --> 01:16:13,345
- Let's hear it.
- Da-hee can go first.

2040
01:16:13,412 --> 01:16:14,646
She wrote so much.

2041
01:16:15,347 --> 01:16:16,515
EVEN AT A GLANCE, THAT IS OBVIOUS

2042
01:16:17,950 --> 01:16:20,185
You did write a lot, Da-hee.

2043
01:16:20,552 --> 01:16:22,554
I SHOULD GET IT OVER WITH
BEFORE I TEAR UP

2044
01:16:23,021 --> 01:16:25,390
- I'll get right on it without fuss.
- Okay.

2045
01:16:25,591 --> 01:16:27,159
"Moments when I was happy
to have housemates.

2046
01:16:27,226 --> 01:16:28,227
Shared meals

2047
01:16:28,293 --> 01:16:30,596
all the little moments
that turned my daily life special

2048
01:16:30,662 --> 01:16:33,432
and the time shared together
on sleepless nights.

2049
01:16:36,235 --> 01:16:38,704
Moments when I was distressed
to have housemates.

2050
01:16:39,071 --> 01:16:41,573
Bathroom breaks, but I got over it."

2051
01:16:42,741 --> 01:16:43,842
- It's so simple.
- Yes.

2052
01:16:43,909 --> 01:16:44,977
- Totally.
- It's almost dry.

2053
01:16:45,043 --> 01:16:46,044
- You like it?
- I do.

2054
01:16:46,111 --> 01:16:47,112
I sure do.

2055
01:16:47,179 --> 01:16:50,115
Don't try anything funny
to make everyone tear up, okay?

2056
01:16:50,182 --> 01:16:51,850
- Yeah, don't do it.
- Okay, let's not do that.

2057
01:16:51,917 --> 01:16:52,918
No one's getting exiled.

2058
01:16:52,985 --> 01:16:54,019
- Right.
- Exactly.

2059
01:16:54,086 --> 01:16:56,155
- We can keep in touch, right?
- Of course.

2060
01:16:57,055 --> 01:17:00,626
"Lastly, please write a comment
for each housemate.

2061
01:17:01,360 --> 01:17:02,594
Do-yeon.

2062
01:17:05,330 --> 01:17:07,866
It was uncomfortable
and awkward at first

2063
01:17:10,135 --> 01:17:14,606
but you were my rock
throughout our journey."

2064
01:17:14,673 --> 01:17:17,342
THE VERY FIRST COMMENT
IS ABOUT TO SET HER OFF

2065
01:17:18,177 --> 01:17:19,444
IS HE TEARING UP?

2066
01:17:19,511 --> 01:17:21,246
SCRATCH, SCRATCH

2067
01:17:21,313 --> 01:17:22,514
My eyebrows feel itchy.

2068
01:17:22,581 --> 01:17:23,649
- What's going on?
- Sorry.

2069
01:17:23,715 --> 01:17:25,150
- What's with you?
- They're so itchy.

2070
01:17:25,217 --> 01:17:27,085
I CAN'T GO ON

2071
01:17:27,152 --> 01:17:28,787
DID SHE JUST RUN AWAY?

2072
01:17:28,854 --> 01:17:30,656
- What's with you?
- They're so itchy.

2073
01:17:30,722 --> 01:17:32,324
- Can I not show my face?
- Of course.

2074
01:17:32,391 --> 01:17:33,525
- Sure.
- Just your voice...

2075
01:17:33,592 --> 01:17:35,561
You can all read yours
at some other place.

2076
01:17:35,627 --> 01:17:37,496
- Just let us hear you.
- It can be embarrassing.

2077
01:17:37,930 --> 01:17:39,131
"Do-yeon.

2078
01:17:39,198 --> 01:17:41,733
It was uncomfortable
and awkward at first

2079
01:17:41,800 --> 01:17:44,303
but you were my rock
throughout our journey.

2080
01:17:45,437 --> 01:17:47,372
I was happy to have you
as my roommate...

2081
01:17:52,644 --> 01:17:53,912
and grateful..."

2082
01:17:54,680 --> 01:17:55,681
Oh, dear.

2083
01:18:01,687 --> 01:18:03,188
My brows are killing me.

2084
01:18:06,525 --> 01:18:13,732
THEY DO THEIR BEST NOT TO TEAR UP

2085
01:18:14,099 --> 01:18:16,235
"I will always remember

2086
01:18:16,802 --> 01:18:18,637
our time together.

2087
01:18:24,610 --> 01:18:25,611
Daniel.

2088
01:18:26,345 --> 01:18:28,347
Just when I was getting used
to your unfiltered chat

2089
01:18:28,413 --> 01:18:30,315
we have to part ways.

2090
01:18:30,549 --> 01:18:32,217
I now have a better grasp

2091
01:18:32,284 --> 01:18:35,320
on your unfiltered thoughts
and the person you are

2092
01:18:35,387 --> 01:18:36,688
and I'm grateful for that.

2093
01:18:36,755 --> 01:18:38,757
Your considerate and caring heart

2094
01:18:38,824 --> 01:18:40,659
made my stay in Gugi-dong
so comfortable

2095
01:18:40,726 --> 01:18:42,060
you wannabe comedian.

2096
01:18:45,464 --> 01:18:46,498
Keun-suk.

2097
01:18:49,534 --> 01:18:51,770
You made every moment special

2098
01:18:51,837 --> 01:18:53,939
living up to your nickname, AP.

2099
01:18:54,006 --> 01:18:55,173
It couldn't have always been easy

2100
01:18:55,240 --> 01:18:56,909
but you never let it show.

2101
01:18:56,975 --> 01:18:58,277
You were so dependable.

2102
01:18:58,677 --> 01:19:00,178
Open up a restaurant someday

2103
01:19:00,245 --> 01:19:01,346
with Soo-jin."

2104
01:19:02,814 --> 01:19:04,549
- We can call it "Sookeun Sookeun."
- Goodness.

2105
01:19:04,616 --> 01:19:05,617
"With Soo-jin."

2106
01:19:05,684 --> 01:19:06,852
THAT DRIED UP HER TEARS

2107
01:19:06,919 --> 01:19:08,520
- We can call it "Sookeun Sookeun."
- Goodness.

2108
01:19:08,587 --> 01:19:09,588
"Sookeun Sookeun."

2109
01:19:09,655 --> 01:19:10,689
WIPING THE TEARS

2110
01:19:11,957 --> 01:19:14,559
LOOK, HE'S CRYING AGAIN

2111
01:19:15,460 --> 01:19:17,596
PUFFY EYES

2112
01:19:18,196 --> 01:19:20,198
That's it for me.

2113
01:19:23,869 --> 01:19:26,071
BACK TO HER ORIGINAL SEAT

2114
01:19:26,371 --> 01:19:27,506
I would also like

2115
01:19:27,572 --> 01:19:29,675
to avoid making it emotional
just because it's our last day.

2116
01:19:30,275 --> 01:19:31,743
- Instead...
- Like you needed to ask.

2117
01:19:31,810 --> 01:19:33,011
- That's tacky!
- Don't do it.

2118
01:19:33,211 --> 01:19:34,680
Let's not be tacky.
We all live in Seoul.

2119
01:19:34,746 --> 01:19:36,281
Yeah, we all live in the city.

2120
01:19:36,348 --> 01:19:37,449
- Yeah.
- Right.

2121
01:19:37,516 --> 01:19:38,717
WHY ARE YOU CRYING, THEN?

2122
01:19:38,784 --> 01:19:39,785
Seriously.

2123
01:19:39,851 --> 01:19:41,586
- You know my style, right?
- Stay true to yourself.

2124
01:19:41,653 --> 01:19:43,055
- All right.
- Seriously.

2125
01:19:43,689 --> 01:19:44,790
"Do-yeon.

2126
01:19:44,856 --> 01:19:47,859
It looked like you usually skip meals
when you're out working.

2127
01:19:47,926 --> 01:19:49,194
I hope you'll try to eat healthy

2128
01:19:49,261 --> 01:19:51,496
when you return home today.

2129
01:19:51,863 --> 01:19:53,465
Daniel.

2130
01:19:53,532 --> 01:19:55,133
I get the feeling
you might talk to the wall

2131
01:19:55,200 --> 01:19:57,436
when you return home.

2132
01:19:57,669 --> 01:20:01,073
Don't do that. Hit me up instead."

2133
01:20:01,640 --> 01:20:03,875
Keun-suk's messages
are about the future.

2134
01:20:03,942 --> 01:20:05,944
- Right.
- Yeah.

2135
01:20:06,011 --> 01:20:07,045
AP LOOKS TOWARD THEIR FUTURE

2136
01:20:07,112 --> 01:20:10,349
"Da-hee. You are
the most meticulous of us all.

2137
01:20:10,582 --> 01:20:11,750
If I get the chance

2138
01:20:11,817 --> 01:20:14,186
I'd love to help you
with your House Squad Goal"

2139
01:20:14,553 --> 01:20:16,388
TOUCHED

2140
01:20:16,455 --> 01:20:17,756
Soo-jin is next.

2141
01:20:18,056 --> 01:20:19,091
"Soo-jin.

2142
01:20:19,424 --> 01:20:21,026
We won't be getting married."

2143
01:20:22,294 --> 01:20:23,295
Just like that?

2144
01:20:23,362 --> 01:20:24,863
DID HE JUST REJECT HER PROPOSAL?

2145
01:20:25,130 --> 01:20:27,866
"But if you need a drinking buddy,
I'll be there."

2146
01:20:29,434 --> 01:20:30,936
- That's the best.
- A rejection

2147
01:20:31,003 --> 01:20:32,437
- followed by an olive branch.
- Exactly.

2148
01:20:32,504 --> 01:20:34,306
I'LL GIVE HIM THAT

2149
01:20:34,539 --> 01:20:35,841
Last but not least, Jae-hyeon.

2150
01:20:36,441 --> 01:20:37,809
"My man, Jae-hyeon.

2151
01:20:37,876 --> 01:20:41,613
I just knew you'd be
such a great friend to me.

2152
01:20:41,680 --> 01:20:42,781
Thank you."

2153
01:20:43,548 --> 01:20:44,549
BESTIES JUST GET EACH OTHER

2154
01:20:44,616 --> 01:20:45,951
- Nice and neat.
- It is nice and neat.

2155
01:20:46,685 --> 01:20:48,620
"To me,
<i>Six Singles Under One Roof </i>was

2156
01:20:48,987 --> 01:20:50,155
not a single photo

2157
01:20:50,222 --> 01:20:51,823
but a roll of film."

2158
01:20:53,692 --> 01:20:54,960
Wow, so sleek.

2159
01:20:55,293 --> 01:20:57,729
THIS IS IT, AP STYLE

2160
01:20:57,796 --> 01:20:59,364
I predicted this, okay?

2161
01:20:59,798 --> 01:21:00,832
MAYBE HE IS SMITTEN?

2162
01:21:00,899 --> 01:21:02,067
- Thanks, guys.
- That was nice.

2163
01:21:02,134 --> 01:21:03,368
It was lovely. It was heartwarming.

2164
01:21:03,602 --> 01:21:04,669
That was nice.

2165
01:21:04,736 --> 01:21:05,937
You had our future in mind.

2166
01:21:06,004 --> 01:21:07,672
Let me wrap up this session.

2167
01:21:07,739 --> 01:21:09,107
LAST IS BRAVE DO-YEON

2168
01:21:09,174 --> 01:21:11,109
- I tried to keep it dry, too.
- Okay.

2169
01:21:11,176 --> 01:21:13,178
"Moments when I was happy
to have housemates.

2170
01:21:13,245 --> 01:21:14,413
Even when I was alone..."

2171
01:21:17,582 --> 01:21:19,384
- What's with you?
- What's up with her?

2172
01:21:19,785 --> 01:21:22,187
Don't be so dramatic.
Come on, Do-yeon.

2173
01:21:22,254 --> 01:21:24,456
I want to look away, too.

2174
01:21:24,523 --> 01:21:27,025
We got choked up, too.
We sucked it up and pulled through.

2175
01:21:27,392 --> 01:21:29,361
I'll stand over here
and read the rest out.

2176
01:21:30,962 --> 01:21:32,364
"Even when I was alone

2177
01:21:32,431 --> 01:21:35,367
I could feel a sense of connection
between us. I loved it."

2178
01:21:44,209 --> 01:21:45,343
Is no one home?

2179
01:21:45,410 --> 01:21:47,012
AS AN INTROVERT

2180
01:21:47,079 --> 01:21:51,283
DO-YEON STRUGGLED WITH BEING
AROUND THE HOUSEMATES THE MOST

2181
01:21:52,617 --> 01:21:54,920
BUT BEING ALONE ONCE AGAIN,
THE TEARS BEGIN TO FALL

2182
01:21:54,986 --> 01:21:56,655
What do I do?

2183
01:21:56,721 --> 01:21:58,423
- I'm sorry.
- What's wrong with you?

2184
01:21:59,891 --> 01:22:03,695
THEY HAVE LONG THOUGHT
THAT SOLITUDE GAVE THEM COMFORT

2185
01:22:03,762 --> 01:22:11,103
BUT PERHAPS THEY WERE
SIMPLY ACCUSTOMED TO IT

2186
01:22:13,538 --> 01:22:15,841
I'm going to read the rest
under the table, too.

2187
01:22:17,542 --> 01:22:18,877
- Under the table?
- Hey.

2188
01:22:20,345 --> 01:22:21,346
Let me start over.

2189
01:22:23,615 --> 01:22:24,616
Sorry, guys.

2190
01:22:24,683 --> 01:22:26,318
- No worries.
- What's going on?

2191
01:22:26,751 --> 01:22:29,087
It's okay.

2192
01:22:29,154 --> 01:22:30,889
I was so sure I wouldn't cry.

2193
01:22:30,956 --> 01:22:33,959
- I thought you wouldn't cry, too.
- Let me try again.

2194
01:22:34,025 --> 01:22:37,295
THE TIME TOGETHER HAS LEFT A MARK
DEEPER THAN ANY OF THEM HAD THOUGHT

2195
01:22:37,996 --> 01:22:40,265
"Moments when I was distressed
to have housemates.

2196
01:22:40,332 --> 01:22:43,902
I loved hanging out with them so much
that it threw off my daily routine."

2197
01:22:45,570 --> 01:22:46,838
That's cute.

2198
01:22:46,905 --> 01:22:47,973
It's pretty adorable.

2199
01:22:48,039 --> 01:22:49,040
That's cute.

2200
01:22:50,308 --> 01:22:52,644
When I try to read the newspaper,
I just can't focus

2201
01:22:52,711 --> 01:22:56,915
because I know
you guys are out the door.

2202
01:22:59,818 --> 01:23:02,154
"Jae-hyeon,
you have the kindest soul.

2203
01:23:06,358 --> 01:23:07,859
Your warm words

2204
01:23:07,926 --> 01:23:09,828
made me love our time here more.

2205
01:23:09,895 --> 01:23:10,896
Thank you.

2206
01:23:17,169 --> 01:23:18,170
Keun-suk.

2207
01:23:18,236 --> 01:23:20,038
You introduce yourself as a freak

2208
01:23:20,105 --> 01:23:22,374
but behind your wild gaze
is a young boy's innocence

2209
01:23:22,674 --> 01:23:25,610
and a generous heart
that finds joy in giving to others.

2210
01:23:25,677 --> 01:23:28,246
I learned so much from you.
Thank you, Keun-suk.

2211
01:23:34,419 --> 01:23:36,755
Soo-jin, you said
you've always wanted an older sister.

2212
01:23:39,090 --> 01:23:42,194
Your smiles are so lovely and warm.

2213
01:23:42,260 --> 01:23:44,863
I will cherish them in my memory.
Thank you.

2214
01:23:50,135 --> 01:23:53,071
Daniel, you said you thought
we might not get along that well.

2215
01:23:53,138 --> 01:23:56,007
But the moment you told me
I had crooked lips

2216
01:23:56,074 --> 01:23:58,743
But the moment you told me
I had crooked lips...

2217
01:24:00,912 --> 01:24:03,782
I sensed that we'd be
the best of friends.

2218
01:24:03,848 --> 01:24:05,951
Thank you for being my friend.

2219
01:24:10,956 --> 01:24:12,891
Just so you know,
my lips aren't crooked.

2220
01:24:12,958 --> 01:24:14,292
The problem is my jaw.

2221
01:24:23,268 --> 01:24:24,436
Last but not least

2222
01:24:25,303 --> 01:24:26,404
sweet Da-hee.

2223
01:24:29,608 --> 01:24:32,210
We practically had to share
our rooms and a bathroom.

2224
01:24:32,277 --> 01:24:34,112
I was sure we'd have
a bumpy ride ahead of us.

2225
01:24:34,713 --> 01:24:36,815
I can't pinpoint when,
but I found myself loving

2226
01:24:36,881 --> 01:24:38,083
your warm presence around me.

2227
01:24:39,584 --> 01:24:41,886
Thank you so much.
All the happiness I felt here

2228
01:24:41,953 --> 01:24:44,222
is all on you. I mean it.

2229
01:24:45,657 --> 01:24:47,859
Thank you so much.
All the happiness I felt here

2230
01:24:47,926 --> 01:24:50,161
is all on you. I mean it."

2231
01:24:50,228 --> 01:24:52,831
DA-HEE HAS TAUGHT DO-YEON
THE WARM COMPANIONSHIP

2232
01:24:52,897 --> 01:24:58,470
THAT ECLIPSES ANY DIFFICULTIES
OF SHARING LIVING QUARTERS

2233
01:24:59,738 --> 01:25:01,740
"To me,
<i>Six Singles Under One Roof </i>was

2234
01:25:02,507 --> 01:25:03,508
like Wi-Fi...

2235
01:25:07,412 --> 01:25:09,481
because we stayed connected."

2236
01:25:09,547 --> 01:25:10,615
That's it.

2237
01:25:14,819 --> 01:25:18,323
THE MOMENT THEY DECIDED
TO LIVE TOGETHER

2238
01:25:18,390 --> 01:25:20,158
- Why are you crying?
- I'm sorry.

2239
01:25:20,225 --> 01:25:24,896
THEY BECAME A FAMILY

2240
01:25:25,964 --> 01:25:27,032
UP NEXT IS SOO-JIN, THE YOUNGEST

2241
01:25:27,098 --> 01:25:30,001
"Moments when I was happy
to have housemates.

2242
01:25:30,068 --> 01:25:31,336
Shared meals

2243
01:25:31,403 --> 01:25:33,905
being taken care of while I was ill

2244
01:25:33,972 --> 01:25:36,308
and messing around together."

2245
01:25:36,574 --> 01:25:38,376
And next.

2246
01:25:38,710 --> 01:25:41,379
"Moments when I was distressed
to have housemates."

2247
01:25:41,446 --> 01:25:44,049
People call it the lonely crowd.

2248
01:25:44,816 --> 01:25:46,151
In all my years of living alone

2249
01:25:47,285 --> 01:25:48,820
In all my years of living alone

2250
01:25:48,887 --> 01:25:50,588
I've never felt alone.

2251
01:25:50,655 --> 01:25:52,123
WHILE LIVING ALONE

2252
01:25:52,190 --> 01:25:55,193
THEY NEVER HAD TO FEEL LONELY

2253
01:25:55,493 --> 01:25:57,362
- Strangely enough
- I feel you.

2254
01:25:57,429 --> 01:25:58,730
when we were together

2255
01:25:58,797 --> 01:26:01,132
I felt more lonesome at times.

2256
01:26:01,199 --> 01:26:03,335
THEY HAVE FINALLY COME TO FEEL LONELY

2257
01:26:04,235 --> 01:26:05,570
"Jae-hyeon.

2258
01:26:05,637 --> 01:26:07,405
You're so tender..."

2259
01:26:07,472 --> 01:26:08,640
Sorry.

2260
01:26:13,311 --> 01:26:15,213
I got choked up for some reason.

2261
01:26:18,550 --> 01:26:19,551
This is hard for me.

2262
01:26:20,452 --> 01:26:22,554
"But you're a manly man
deep down inside."

2263
01:26:23,688 --> 01:26:24,723
I see you figured it out.

2264
01:26:27,592 --> 01:26:28,827
"Keun-suk.

2265
01:26:29,494 --> 01:26:30,962
Here's to our future."

2266
01:26:32,263 --> 01:26:33,765
- For real?
- Did you really write that down?

2267
01:26:34,399 --> 01:26:36,034
- For real?
- Did you really write that down?

2268
01:26:37,001 --> 01:26:40,038
IT'S REAL
KEUN-SUK, HERE'S TO OUR FUTURE

2269
01:26:40,105 --> 01:26:41,506
MISCHIEVOUS SOO-JIN
HASN'T GIVEN UP YET

2270
01:26:41,573 --> 01:26:42,707
Moving on.

2271
01:26:43,408 --> 01:26:46,344
SOLEMN SILENCE FALLS AGAIN

2272
01:26:46,644 --> 01:26:47,779
Let's get going.

2273
01:26:49,848 --> 01:26:50,882
- Let's go.
- Shall we?

2274
01:26:50,949 --> 01:26:51,950
- We'd better.
- We should go.

2275
01:26:52,016 --> 01:26:53,017
- Okay.
- Okay.

2276
01:26:53,485 --> 01:26:56,254
- Let's leave without hesitation.
- Okay.

2277
01:26:56,321 --> 01:26:57,722
Are all your things packed up?

2278
01:26:57,789 --> 01:26:59,057
- Sure.
- Of course.

2279
01:27:00,325 --> 01:27:02,527
REMAINING TIME
UNTIL THEIR LEASE EXPIRES

2280
01:27:02,594 --> 01:27:07,065
30 MINUTES

2281
01:27:07,132 --> 01:27:09,167
We're all in our 40s

2282
01:27:09,901 --> 01:27:11,403
and we've been living together

2283
01:27:12,170 --> 01:27:13,605
for a while.

2284
01:27:13,838 --> 01:27:15,573
And before leaving,
we just read some letters.

2285
01:27:15,640 --> 01:27:17,108
But boy, did I cry a lot.

2286
01:27:17,642 --> 01:27:19,577
I figured it was just business.

2287
01:27:19,644 --> 01:27:20,812
Turns out we were all sincere.

2288
01:27:21,746 --> 01:27:23,515
<i>When I'm at home</i>

2289
01:27:24,149 --> 01:27:26,017
<i>I'm rather like stainless steel.</i>

2290
01:27:26,651 --> 01:27:28,486
<i>I rarely have mood swings</i>

2291
01:27:29,220 --> 01:27:30,989
or an occasion to put myself
in other people's shoes.

2292
01:27:31,456 --> 01:27:33,124
I never have to do something
for others either

2293
01:27:33,191 --> 01:27:34,359
because I'm alone.

2294
01:27:34,426 --> 01:27:36,361
But during my time here

2295
01:27:36,428 --> 01:27:38,029
I had so many moments

2296
01:27:38,096 --> 01:27:40,064
when my heart melted

2297
01:27:40,131 --> 01:27:41,933
and grew tender.

2298
01:27:42,000 --> 01:27:43,168
It was almost like

2299
01:27:43,501 --> 01:27:45,570
I became a living being

2300
01:27:45,937 --> 01:27:48,373
like a plant or an animal.

2301
01:27:52,844 --> 01:27:54,679
<i>I think you turn</i>
<i>into a coward after 40.</i>

2302
01:27:54,746 --> 01:27:56,815
<i>You're hesitant</i>
<i>to open your heart to someone</i>

2303
01:27:56,881 --> 01:27:58,950
<i>or close it up again.</i>

2304
01:27:59,017 --> 01:28:00,885
<i>You're too afraid</i>
<i>to make those choices.</i>

2305
01:28:05,023 --> 01:28:08,860
I was slowly losing the confidence
to open up my heart.

2306
01:28:08,927 --> 01:28:11,129
My housemates

2307
01:28:11,196 --> 01:28:13,531
gave me so much courage

2308
01:28:13,598 --> 01:28:16,601
and strength

2309
01:28:16,668 --> 01:28:19,204
to help me put myself out there.

2310
01:28:19,270 --> 01:28:20,572
KEUN-SUK FOUND THE COURAGE
TO OPEN UP AGAIN

2311
01:28:20,638 --> 01:28:21,940
Do you guys remember

2312
01:28:22,407 --> 01:28:24,776
that dance game we played
after trying Pu*p It Up?

2313
01:28:24,843 --> 01:28:26,644
- J*** Dance?
- Was that it?

2314
01:28:26,711 --> 01:28:28,480
Want to go out dancing
to leave things on a high note?

2315
01:28:29,113 --> 01:28:30,949
- How did the dance go?
- Something like this?

2316
01:28:31,015 --> 01:28:32,350
- Like so?
- Did we have this move?

2317
01:28:32,550 --> 01:28:35,119
- Let's go out with a bang.
- Let's do that!

2318
01:28:36,888 --> 01:28:37,889
That's the spirit.

2319
01:28:37,956 --> 01:28:39,090
LET'S LEAVE WITH A BIG SMILE

2320
01:28:39,157 --> 01:28:40,158
Let's not cry.

2321
01:28:43,661 --> 01:28:45,063
Seriously, guys.

2322
01:28:45,129 --> 01:28:46,564
A GROUP OF NEW FRIENDS
BY THE NAME OF GUGI-DONG FAMILY

2323
01:28:46,631 --> 01:28:49,434
HAS ENTERED THEIR SOLITARY DAYS

2324
01:28:49,501 --> 01:28:51,035
- Should I turn this off?
- Yeah.

2325
01:28:57,809 --> 01:29:01,012
BETWEEN SOLITUDE AND WILD NOISE

2326
01:29:01,079 --> 01:29:04,983
BETWEEN DISCOMFORT AND WARMTH

2327
01:29:05,750 --> 01:29:08,086
WILL WE EVER GET
TO LIVE TOGETHER AGAIN?

2328
01:29:08,152 --> 01:29:11,589
WE CAN DO THAT WHENEVER YOU'RE LONELY

2329
01:29:11,656 --> 01:29:14,192
STAY TUNED FOR AN EPILOGUE

2330
01:29:14,459 --> 01:29:16,995
I unknowingly cleared
another House Squad Goal.

2331
01:29:17,061 --> 01:29:18,062
- What?
- What is it?

2332
01:29:18,129 --> 01:29:19,130
- An album?
- An album?

2333
01:29:19,197 --> 01:29:21,766
A FAMILY ALBUM FILLED WITH MEMORIES
PREPARED AS A PARTING GIFT

2334
01:29:21,833 --> 01:29:24,335
- That's crazy.
- It's literally a family album.

2335
01:29:26,971 --> 01:29:28,640
<i>"First dinner for Gugi-dong fam."</i>

2336
01:29:28,706 --> 01:29:30,108
<i>That's cute. "Team Octopus for life."</i>

2337
01:29:30,174 --> 01:29:31,543
<i>How clever.</i>

2338
01:29:31,609 --> 01:29:33,411
MEMORIES PLAY IN THEIR MINDS
LIKE FRAMES ON A FILM REEL

2339
01:29:33,478 --> 01:29:34,979
There's our highlight.

2340
01:29:35,513 --> 01:29:36,514
SLAPSTICK BROUGHT US TOGETHER

2341
01:29:36,581 --> 01:29:38,082
"This is what I'm talking about."

2342
01:29:38,149 --> 01:29:40,218
MEMORIES COMING BACK

2343
01:29:40,685 --> 01:29:42,620
Dude, I look so silly here.

2344
01:29:43,187 --> 01:29:44,222
PHOTOS OF DANIEL'S BIRTHDAY

2345
01:29:44,289 --> 01:29:47,025
<i>Check out the photo with the cake.</i>
<i>When you look closely</i>

2346
01:29:47,091 --> 01:29:48,560
<i>- you can see tears in his eyes.</i>
<i>- Totally.</i>

2347
01:29:48,626 --> 01:29:49,794
<i>He got teary.</i>

2348
01:29:50,528 --> 01:29:51,529
PHOTOS BECOME MEMORIES

2349
01:29:51,596 --> 01:29:54,566
<i>Our time together was warm.</i>

2350
01:29:54,632 --> 01:29:55,867
AND MEMORIES MADE THEM ONE

2351
01:29:56,467 --> 01:29:58,636
- "Odd eyes."
<i>- Our time together brought me</i>

2352
01:29:58,703 --> 01:30:01,906
<i>unexpected joy,</i>
<i>touching moments, warmth</i>

2353
01:30:01,973 --> 01:30:03,308
<i>and dependable friends.</i>

2354
01:30:03,708 --> 01:30:05,143
<i>I'm glad I joined this show.</i>

2355
01:30:05,543 --> 01:30:07,712
<i>I've learned that small comforts</i>

2356
01:30:07,779 --> 01:30:11,015
<i>could be turning points</i>
<i>that change your life forever.</i>

2357
01:30:11,950 --> 01:30:14,218
"Even if I could turn back time,
I wouldn't trade these memories.

2358
01:30:14,285 --> 01:30:16,487
Goodbye, my dear Gugi-dong fam."

2359
01:30:16,554 --> 01:30:17,555
That's the sign-off.

2360
01:30:17,889 --> 01:30:21,125
GOODBYE!

2361
01:30:21,326 --> 01:30:23,328
Subtitles by Jeongwoo Kim
